Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.45,0:02:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{{\fn新宋体\fs8\fscy95\i1\bord0\shad3\c&HFFFFFF&\4c&H000000&\4a&H2C&\fad(800,700)\pos(193,167.667)}导 演\N\N{\fs11}奥莉维娅·纽曼
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.88,0:02:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn新宋体\fs14\fscy95\bord0\fad(600,600)\c&HFDFDFD&\4c&H000000&\4a&H2E&\pos(130.8,240.2)}北卡罗莱纳州 巴克利湾
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.62,0:02:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn新宋体\fs15\fscy80\bord0\fad(600,600)\4c&H000000&\4a&H2E&\pos(96.8,240)\c&HF6F6F6&}1969年10月30日
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.55,0:02:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}沼泽地对死亡了如指掌...\N{\reng\i1}A swamp knows all about death...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.84,0:03:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但不一定将其视为悲剧\N{\reng\i1}and doesn't necessarily define it as tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.39,0:03:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当然也不是罪\N{\reng\i1}Certainly not a sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.62,0:03:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为蔡斯·安德鲁斯会有更多的常识\N{\reng}I thought Chase Andrews would have more common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.15,0:03:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,本镇有史以来最好的四分卫\N{\reng}Best quarterback this town ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.87,0:03:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,孩子们 这些是你们踩的脚印吗?\N{\reng}Boys, are these your footprints here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.72,0:03:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 警官\N{\reng}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.80,0:03:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他的脚印在哪里?\N{\reng}Where's his footprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.00,0:03:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 有些孩子脑子里就有疯狂的想法\N{\reng}Yeah, some kids just get crazy ideas in their heads
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.45,0:03:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,喝了酒就觉得自己是无敌的\N{\reng}and drink and think they're invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.55,0:03:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,蔡斯·安德鲁斯不是孩子\N{\reng}That Chase Andrews was no Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.72,0:03:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 看看这个\N{\reng}Hey. Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.42,0:04:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他自己打开了栅栏?  - 可能又是意外 都一样\N{\reng}- He open the grate himself?  - Could've been an accident, all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.32,0:04:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,死亡时间 在午夜到凌晨2点之间\N{\reng}Time of death, between midnight and 2 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.75,0:04:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,死亡原因 从63英尺高空坠落的冲击力\N{\reng}Cause of death, sudden impact from the 63-foot drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.25,0:04:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,既然你发现了支撑梁上的血迹和头发\N{\reng}Since you found that blood and hair on the support beam,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.35,0:04:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,那就可以推断出这是造成主要伤害的原因\N{\reng}I would deduce that was the cause of the primary injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.40,0:04:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,通俗点说 就是他在下坠过程中撞到了后脑勺\N{\reng}Laymen's terms, he banged the back of his head on the way down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.05,0:04:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,要把后脑勺撞到横梁上\N{\reng}To hit the back of his head on the beam,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.70,0:04:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,他必须向后倒下 是这样吗?\N{\reng}he would've needed to fall backwards, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.95,0:04:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是的  - 所以他可能是被推下去的\N{\reng}- I'd say yes.  - So he might have been pushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.32,0:04:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,栏杆 栅栏上都没有指纹 什么都没有\N{\reng}There's no fingerprints on the railing, the grates, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.00,0:04:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,没有指纹? 也没有蔡斯的?\N{\reng}No fingerprints? Not from Chase either?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.77,0:04:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,没有指纹 没有划痕\N{\reng}No fingerprints, no tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们确实在夹克上发现了那些红色纤维\N{\reng}We do have those red fibers found on the jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.75,0:04:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚刚从亚特兰大拿回实验室报告\N{\reng}I just got the lab report back from Atlanta.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.17,0:05:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,它们不是来自他的其它任何衣服\N{\reng}They did not come from any of his other clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.46,0:05:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,羊毛 报告说可能是件毛衣 围巾\N{\reng}Wool, it says. That could be a sweater, scarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.05,0:05:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,见鬼 可能是任何东西\N{\reng}Hell, it could be anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.05,0:05:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须找到它\N{\reng}And we gotta find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.52,0:05:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,有个漂亮的妻子 良好的家庭 想不出有谁想杀蔡斯\N{\reng}A beautiful wife, good family. Can't think of anyone who'd want to kill Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.35,0:05:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,得了吧 你知道蔡斯是怎样的人\N{\reng}Come on. You know how Chase was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.23,0:05:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,滥交男 像头被放出的圈养公牛一样到处发情\N{\reng}Tomcattin', ruttin' around like a penned-up bull let out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.20,0:05:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,不要评判死者 弗兰克\N{\reng}Don't speak ill of the dead, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是说说能想到的几个这种人\N{\reng}I'm just saying I could think of a few guys up to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- 米尔顿先生  - 嗨 桑迪\N{\reng}- Mr. Milton.  - Hi, Sandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.77,0:05:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 老样子? 布朗斯维克炖肉?  - 猜对了\N{\reng}- The usual? Brunswick stew?  - How'd you guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.50,0:05:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你对蔡斯·安德鲁斯的案子怎么看 汤姆?\N{\reng}What do you make of the Chase Andrews case, Tom?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.22,0:05:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 我退休了 这不是我关心的了\N{\reng}Oh, I'm retired. That's none of my business anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.30,0:05:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- 有道理  - 可能是沼泽里那个女人\N{\reng}- Fair enough.  - Could've been that woman in the marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.02,0:05:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,她的疯狂足以让她进疯人院 我打赌她做得出这种事\N{\reng}She's crazy enough for the loony bin. I bet she'd be up to something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.25,0:05:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我哥哥说沼泽女孩是缺失的一环\N{\reng}My brother's told me that Marsh Girl's the missing link.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.07,0:05:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道可怜的蔡斯·安德鲁斯死在了那片沼泽地里\N{\reng}You know poor Chase Andrews had something going on down in that marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.02,0:05:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,蔡斯·安德鲁斯和沼泽女孩? 他在自找麻烦\N{\reng}Chase Andrews and the Marsh Girl? Now if that ain't asking for trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.47,0:05:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得真正发生了什么 弗兰克?\N{\reng}What do you think really happened, Frank?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,会是沼泽女孩杀了蔡斯吗?\N{\reng}You think that Marsh Girl killed Chase?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.17,0:05:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,见鬼 我也不知道 真相会出来的\N{\reng}Hell, I don't know. Truth will come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,看看这些羽毛和其他东西\N{\reng}Look at all these feathers and whatnot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.77,0:06:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,她是科学家还是女巫?\N{\reng}She a scientist or a witch?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.55,0:06:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,克拉克小姐?\N{\reng}Miss Clark?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.30,0:06:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- 治安部门  - 警长\N{\reng}- Sheriff's Department.  - Sheriff.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.20,0:06:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,看\N{\reng}Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.90,0:06:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,可以申请搜查令了\N{\reng}Could get a warrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.85,0:06:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,显而易见 有足够理由 警长\N{\reng}Plain view. Probable cause, sheriff.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.82,0:06:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我打赌那道门没有锁\N{\reng}Bet that door isn't even locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.65,0:07:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,她在那里\N{\reng}There she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.62,0:07:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们是治安部门 关掉你的引擎\N{\reng\i1}This is the Sheriff's Department. Shut down your engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.32,0:08:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,直走 往前走 跟着她\N{\reng}Go straight, go straight. Follow her in!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你有罪  - 你杀了蔡斯·安德鲁斯\N{\reng}- You're guilty!  - You killed Chase Andrews!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.35,0:08:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你会为此付出代价  - 牢底坐穿\N{\reng}- You'll pay for this!  - Rot in jail!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,贾斯蒂斯 你要去哪里 猫咪?\N{\reng}Sunday Justice. Where you gone, kitty?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.65,0:09:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,请留下\N{\reng}Please stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.52,0:09:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,过来 猫咪\N{\reng}Here, kitty, kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.77,0:09:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,克拉克小姐?\N{\reng}Miss Clark?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.77,0:09:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我是汤姆·米尔顿\N{\reng}I'm Tom Milton.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.85,0:09:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我是律师 我可以进来吗?\N{\reng}I'm a lawyer. May I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.24,0:09:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 弗雷泽警官\N{\reng}Thank you, Mr. Frazier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.27,0:09:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能知道 你因谋杀蔡斯·安德鲁斯被拘押\N{\reng}You probably know that you're being held for the murder of Chase Andrews.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.13,0:09:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我冒昧的提出要为你辩护\N{\reng}And I have taken the liberty of putting myself forward to defend you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.07,0:09:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你以前从未遇到过麻烦\N{\reng}I know you've never been in trouble before,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.02,0:10:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我可以解释法庭和审判以及谁是谁之类的问题\N{\reng}so I can explain the courtroom and the trial and who is who and whatnot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.85,0:10:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,呃 你有家人吗 你可能希望他们来陪你?\N{\reng}Uh, do you have family that you might want to come be with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.00,0:10:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,克拉克小姐 我不知道该怎么说 但是 呃... ...\N{\reng}Miss Clark, I don't quite know how to put this, but, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.47,0:10:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 我知道你叫凯瑟琳·丹尼尔·克拉克\N{\reng}Well, I know you as Catherine Danielle Clark,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.90,0:10:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但在巴克利湾 大家不叫你这个名字\N{\reng}but here in Barkley Cove they don't call you by that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.87,0:10:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,他们叫你沼泽女孩\N{\reng}They call you Marsh Girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.62,0:10:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,而当你受审时\N{\reng}And when you stand trial,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.50,0:10:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你将由来自巴克利湾的居民\N{\reng}you will be judged by a jury of your peers
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.22,0:10:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,组成的陪审团审判 他们只知道你这个绰号\N{\reng}from Barkley Cove, who only know you as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,无论他们是否了解你 他们都会对你进行审判\N{\reng}They are going to judge you whether they know you or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.32,0:10:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,除非我能了解你 不然我没法帮你\N{\reng}But I can't help you unless I know you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.95,0:10:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,哪怕只是一点点\N{\reng}Even just a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.15,0:11:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 好吧 那么 呃...\N{\reng}Well, all right, then. Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.20,0:11:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,等你有时间考虑后 我再来\N{\reng}I'll come back in a while when you've had time to consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.45,0:11:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 我给你带了一本书来打发时间\N{\reng}Oh, and I brought you this just in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.12,0:11:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,弗拉齐尔警官\N{\reng}Mr. Frazier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.87,0:11:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,人们忘记了那些生活在贝壳里的生物\N{\reng}People forget about the creatures who live in shells.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.70,0:11:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾经有家庭\N{\reng}I had a family once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.65,0:11:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们叫我凯雅\N{\reng}They called me Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.87,0:11:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.47,0:11:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 你最好不要跑得太远\N{\reng}Kya! You'd better not get too far out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.66,0:11:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,抓住它 抓住它\N{\reng}Get it, get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.82,0:12:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,现在这只小猪去了市场 现在你不要动\N{\reng}Now this little piggy went to market. Now you hold still.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.20,0:12:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,这只小猪待在家里\N{\reng}This little piggy stayed home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.75,0:12:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这只小猪吃了烤牛肉\N{\reng}This little piggy ate roast beef.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.77,0:12:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,这只小猪没吃饭\N{\reng}This little piggy had none.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.40,0:12:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,这只小猪在回家的路上一直哭哭啼啼\N{\reng}And this little piggy went wee-wee-wee-wee all the way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.35,0:12:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我的宝贝女儿\N{\reng}That's my special girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.60,0:12:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 乔迪\N{\reng}Hey, Jodie!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.72,0:12:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 泰特\N{\reng}Hey, Tate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.30,0:12:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,想来钓鱼吗?\N{\reng}Wanna come fishing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.67,0:12:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我没有多余时间  - “没有”不是个实词\N{\reng}- I ain't got too much time.  - "Ain't" isn't a real word.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.97,0:12:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 我说过多少次别在我的船上捣乱?\N{\reng}Hey, how many times I told you not to mess in my goddamn boat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.42,0:12:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,进屋去 你傻了吗?\N{\reng}Get in the house! Are you stupid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.87,0:13:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,过来 现在你已经做了\N{\reng}Come here! Now you've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.65,0:13:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须学会尊重 听到了吗?\N{\reng}You gotta learn respect. You hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.12,0:13:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 住手 你在伤害她  - 嘿 你别烦我爸爸\N{\reng}- Stop it! You're hurting her!  - Hey, you leave my pa alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.15,0:13:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,再来我这里 我就开枪打你 听到了吗?\N{\reng}Come back on my land, I'll shoot you! You hear me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.67,0:13:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 冷静点  - 闭嘴\N{\reng}- Calm down now.  - Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.21,0:13:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,闭嘴\N{\reng}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.09,0:13:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- 别烦我  - 我会给你看\N{\reng}- Leave me alone!  - I'll show you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.07,0:13:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,请停下\N{\reng}Please just stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.32,0:14:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈\N{\reng}Ma!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.87,0:14:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈?\N{\reng}Ma?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.17,0:14:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}妈妈再也没有回来\N{\reng\i1}Ma never came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.50,0:14:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}其他人也很快以同样的方式走了\N{\reng\i1}And everybody else was quick to get out the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.05,0:14:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}墨菲是最先离开的\N{\reng\i1}Murph was the first to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.67,0:14:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}几个月后 是曼迪和米茜\N{\reng\i1}A few months later, Mandy and Missy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.82,0:14:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}接着 最后是朱迪\N{\reng\i1}Then, finally, Jodie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.37,0:14:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.97,0:14:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 听着\N{\reng}Kya, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.22,0:14:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我得走了 凯雅 我没法再住在这里了\N{\reng}I have to go, Kya. I can't live here no longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.27,0:14:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 要小心 听到了吗?\N{\reng}Kya, you be careful, hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.64,0:14:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你遇到麻烦\N{\reng}If you're in trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.15,0:14:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,就跑到沼泽深处喇蛄唱歌的地方躲起来\N{\reng}run and hide deep in the marsh way out where the crawdads sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.30,0:15:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,就像妈妈一直说的\N{\reng}Like Ma always says.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.65,0:15:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,快跑\N{\reng}Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.47,0:15:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,乔迪\N{\reng}Jodie!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.92,0:15:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我从其他人的错误中学会了如何与父亲生活\N{\reng\i1}I learned from the mistakes of the others how to live with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.15,0:15:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只要别碍着他\N{\reng\i1}Just keep out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.47,0:15:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}别让他看到你\N{\reng\i1}Don't let him see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.75,0:15:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}自己照顾自己\N{\reng\i1}Fend for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.52,0:16:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我和朱迪在沼泽地里待过很多次 但从没有单独去过\N{\reng\i1}I had been out in the marsh plenty of times with Jodie, but never alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.35,0:16:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不知道哪条路回家\N{\reng\i1}I didn't know which way was home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.65,0:16:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你把我丢下真该死 朱迪\N{\reng}Damn you for leaving me here, Jodie!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.65,0:16:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你真该死\N{\reng}Damn you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.47,0:16:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗?\N{\reng}You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.37,0:17:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你是朱迪·克拉克的妹妹\N{\reng}You're Jodie Clark's sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.60,0:17:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,曾经是 他已经走了\N{\reng}Used to be. He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.10,0:17:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你知道回家的路吗?  - 知道\N{\reng}- You know your way home?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.45,0:17:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,没事 我经常会迷路\N{\reng}It's okay. I get lost all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.90,0:17:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫泰特 万一你再见到我\N{\reng}My name's Tate, in case you see me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}泰特\N{\reng\i1}Tate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.17,0:17:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那个男孩身上有些东西能让我感到放松\N{\reng\i1}There was something about that boy that eased the tightness in my chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.32,0:17:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是妈妈和朱迪离开后的第一次\N{\reng\i1}For the first time since Ma and Jodie left,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.97,0:17:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我感觉到除伤害之外的其他东西\N{\reng\i1}I felt something other than hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.35,0:17:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我感觉到勇气\N{\reng\i1}I felt brave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.17,0:17:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我饿了\N{\reng}I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.50,0:18:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,早 克拉克先生 你还好吗?\N{\reng}Morning, Mr. Clark. How you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.20,0:18:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 朱姆平 我是在泥地的右边醒来的\N{\reng}Well, Jumpin', I woke up on the right side of dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.02,0:18:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我女儿 凯雅·克拉克\N{\reng}Oh, this is my daughter, Miss Kya Clark.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.62,0:18:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 很荣幸认识你 凯雅小姐\N{\reng}Well, I'm mighty proud to know you, Miss Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.90,0:18:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,别管她 我告诉她要离所有人都远点\N{\reng}Oh, don't mind her. I tell her, uh, stay away from everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.22,0:18:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是个危险的世界 不是吗?  - 没错 但适合钓鱼\N{\reng}- It's a dangerous world, isn't it?  - It is. But the fishing's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.97,0:18:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,能否给我一袋燕麦片?\N{\reng}Could I get a bag of grits?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.52,0:18:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,来几瓶占边酒?\N{\reng}And some of that Jim Beam?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.22,0:18:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- 再帮我把油箱加满?  - 没问题\N{\reng}- And maybe you fill her up for me?  - It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.60,0:18:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- 梅布尔  - 嗯\N{\reng}- Mabel.  - Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.17,0:18:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你等着拿零钱 听到了吗?\N{\reng}You wait for our change, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.95,0:18:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你妈妈不在的时候你帮你爸爸吗?\N{\reng}Helping out your pa while your ma's gone, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.95,0:18:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我有阵子没见到她了\N{\reng}I ain't seen her in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.15,0:18:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 她在家里做家务  - 他\N{\reng}- She's doing chores at home.  - Mm-him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.07,0:19:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,燕麦片不能当饭吃\N{\reng}Grits ain't much to go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.67,0:19:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我们看看这里\N{\reng}All right. Let's see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.52,0:19:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你爸爸留下2美元\N{\reng}Your pa left $2 here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.02,0:19:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,账单是1.5美元\N{\reng}And the bill is $1.50.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.82,0:19:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,那剩下的汽油钱是多少?\N{\reng}How much does that leave for gas?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.02,0:19:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,不用管这个\N{\reng}Don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.35,0:19:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我还有个问题要问你\N{\reng}I got another question for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.92,0:19:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你在上学吗 亲爱的?\N{\reng}You go to school, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.95,0:19:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道他们在报纸上公布学校的午餐菜单吗?\N{\reng}Do you know that they publish the school lunch menu in the paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.57,0:19:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,今天的是...\N{\reng}Today's is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.32,0:19:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,索尔兹伯里牛排\N{\reng}Salisbury steak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.05,0:19:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以吃到一顿美味的热饭 交一些朋友\N{\reng}You could get a nice, hot meal, make some friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.45,0:19:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,很多孩子上学时都没有穿鞋\N{\reng}Plenty of kids go to school without shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.40,0:19:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,但你需要一条裙子\N{\reng}But you will need a skirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.17,0:19:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,问你妈妈要一条\N{\reng}Ask your mama for one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:19:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,好了\N{\reng}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.37,0:19:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,零钱是50美分\N{\reng}And the change is 50 cents.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.02,0:20:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,孩子们\N{\reng}Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.97,0:20:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,蔡斯·安德鲁斯 这就是你的礼貌吗?\N{\reng}Chase Andrews, what you got to say for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.45,0:20:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 潘西小姐\N{\reng}Sorry, Miss Pansy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.12,0:20:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,那个女孩挡住了路 我们没有看到你\N{\reng}We didn't see you 'cause that girl got in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.67,0:20:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\reng}Hello there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.97,0:20:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你走错了方向 小姑娘\N{\reng}I think you've got yourself turned around the wrong way, little lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.70,0:21:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,学校不是走这边吗?\N{\reng}Isn't school that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.17,0:21:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好脏啊  - 真恶心\N{\reng}- So dirty.  - Gross.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.25,0:21:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你有同样的权利去上学\N{\reng}You have just as much of a right to be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.75,0:21:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,现在就去吧 没事的\N{\reng}Go along now. It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.81,0:21:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳·丹尼尔·克拉克小姐 你已经会阅读和写字了吗?\N{\reng}Miss Catherine Danielle Clark, are you reading and writing already?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.80,0:21:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你能拼出“狗”吗 亲爱的?\N{\reng}Can you spell "dog," honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.78,0:21:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,那是谁?\N{\reng}Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.72,0:21:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝\N{\reng}G-O-D.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.62,0:21:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我们都可以练习 不是吗?\N{\reng}Well, we can all use practice, can't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.62,0:21:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你过去坐下吧 凯瑟琳·丹尼尔·克拉克小姐\N{\reng}You can go ahead and sit down, Miss Catherine Danielle Clark.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.00,0:21:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你去哪里了 沼泽鸡?\N{\reng}Where you been, marsh hen?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.60,0:21:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你的帽子呢 沼泽鼠?\N{\reng}Where's your hat, swamp rat?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.22,0:21:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,孩子们 安静下来 离午餐只有一个小时了\N{\reng}Now, boys and girls, settle down. Just an hour until lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.12,0:21:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,请尽量专心听课\N{\reng}Please, try to pay attention to our lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.70,0:21:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,谁能告诉我一个有长元音的词吗?\N{\reng}Who can tell me a word that has a long vowel sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.92,0:22:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- 她可能住在泥地里  - 她身上有虱子\N{\reng}- She probably lives in the mud.  - Someone's got cooties.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.90,0:22:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,教室里有股臭味\N{\reng}That stink in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.85,0:22:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,请原谅\N{\reng}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.25,0:22:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那是我在学校度过的唯一一天\N{\reng\i1}That was the only day I ever spent in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.77,0:22:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我觉得我从野外学习比较好\N{\reng\i1}Reckoned I was better off learning from the wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.67,0:22:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 泰特\N{\reng}Hi, Tate!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.27,0:22:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\reng}Mm-mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.72,0:22:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你在外面要小心 听到了吗?\N{\reng}Need you to be careful out here. You hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.30,0:22:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能相信任何人\N{\reng}You can't trust nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.67,0:22:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你要保护自己\N{\reng}You protect yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.20,0:22:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,可能是大角猫头鹰\N{\reng}Great horned owl, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.02,0:23:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有段时间 爸爸对我很好\N{\reng\i1}For a while, Pa was good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.64,0:23:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你可以用这个来装你的羽毛 鸟窝\N{\reng}Ahem. I thought you could use this for your feathers, bird nests.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.20,0:23:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你收集的其他东西\N{\reng}Other stuff you collect.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.65,0:23:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- 噢 谢谢  - 嗯\N{\reng}- Oh, thank you.  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.72,0:23:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是我的旧军...  - 邮件\N{\reng}- It was my old Army...  - Mail!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.32,0:23:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,是我的旧军队背包\N{\reng}It's my old Army knapsack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.20,0:23:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,是妈妈给我的 妈妈给我的\N{\reng}It's from Ma! It's from Ma!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.25,0:23:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,是妈妈的笔迹\N{\reng}It's Ma's handwriting!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.47,0:23:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 妈妈还活着  - 把它给我\N{\reng}- Ma's alive!  - Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.30,0:23:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,把它给我\N{\reng}Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.57,0:24:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- 她什么时候回家?  - 等等\N{\reng}- When's she coming home?  - Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.17,0:24:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,她说什么了?\N{\reng}What does she say?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.72,0:24:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不  - 安静\N{\reng}- No!  - Quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.97,0:24:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,爸 爸爸 停下\N{\reng}Pa! Pa, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.72,0:24:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,停下 别烧\N{\reng}Stop it! Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.22,0:24:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- 停下  - 安静 安静\N{\reng}- Stop!  - Quiet. Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.35,0:24:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈\N{\reng}Ma.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.54,0:24:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,现在你听我说\N{\reng}Now you listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.52,0:24:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,她再也不会回来了\N{\reng}She ain't never coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.17,0:24:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你听到了吗?\N{\reng}You hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.67,0:24:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是真的\N{\reng}That isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.50,0:24:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“不会”都不是个实词\N{\reng}"Ain't" isn't even a real word!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.37,0:24:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,该死的贱人\N{\reng}Goddamn bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.83,0:24:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,没用的\N{\reng}Useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.58,0:25:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}爸爸烧掉任何有妈妈痕迹的东西\N{\reng\i1}Pa took to burning any trace of Ma.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.37,0:25:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,把你的东西拿出去\N{\reng}Get your shit out of my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.97,0:25:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然后有一天...\N{\reng\i1}And then one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.60,0:25:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他也走了\N{\reng\i1}he was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.35,0:25:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不像妈妈离开时那样难过\N{\reng\i1}Wasn't like the pain when Ma left.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.32,0:25:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但完全孤独感是如此之大 它回荡着\N{\reng\i1}But being completely alone was a feeling so vast, it echoed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.75,0:25:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有个小问题 就是生存\N{\reng\i1}And there was the small matter of surviving.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.27,0:25:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我还没有学会没有燕麦片的生活\N{\reng\i1}I didn't know how to do life without grits.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.32,0:26:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 你好 凯雅小姐\N{\reng}Well, hello, Miss Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.27,0:26:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你想要什么吗?\N{\reng}You want something?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.27,0:26:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,朱姆平先生...\N{\reng}Mr. Jumpin'...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.97,0:26:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我听说你们要买贻贝\N{\reng}I hear tell y'all buy mussels.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.02,0:26:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我这里有一些\N{\reng}I got some here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.55,0:26:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 新鲜吗?  - 黎明前挖的\N{\reng}- They fresh?  - Dug them before dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.25,0:26:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,就是刚才\N{\reng}Just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.80,0:26:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你爸爸让你带这些东西出来?\N{\reng}Your pa sent you out with these?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.67,0:26:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我跟你说 我给你50美分一袋\N{\reng}Look, I tell you what, I'll give you 50 cent for the one bag
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.00,0:26:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,另一袋给一满箱油\N{\reng}and a full tank of gas for the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.99,0:26:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你们一周需要多少袋?\N{\reng}How many bags y'all need a week?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.20,0:26:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是在做生意吗?\N{\reng}Are we striking up a business deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.57,0:27:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我每两三天买一次 大约40磅\N{\reng}I buy about 40 pound every two, three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.65,0:27:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,提醒你 其他人也会拿来\N{\reng}Mind you, others bring them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.37,0:27:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 如果你拿来 而我已经买了\N{\reng}So if you bring them, and I already got some,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.55,0:27:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你就出局了\N{\reng}why, you'd just be out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.30,0:27:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,这是先来后到 没有其他办法\N{\reng}It's first come, first served. Ain't no other way of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.02,0:27:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这样很好 谢谢你\N{\reng}That's fine. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.65,0:27:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以吗?\N{\reng}Can I, uh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.97,0:27:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 可以\N{\reng}Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.40,0:27:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你确实长得很快 是吧?\N{\reng}You sure are growing up fast, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.72,0:27:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你在下周过来 我给你量一下脚\N{\reng}Why don't you come by next week, I'll measure your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.40,0:27:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我在教堂的捐赠箱里有些鞋子 都在吃灰\N{\reng}I got some shoes in the church donation bin just collecting dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.67,0:27:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢你 女士  - 好说\N{\reng}- Thank you, ma'am.  - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.25,0:28:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,可怜的孩子\N{\reng}Poor child.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.57,0:28:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,她妈妈走了 我肯定现在她爸爸也走了\N{\reng}Her ma's gone, and now her pa's gone too, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.45,0:28:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,什么?\N{\reng}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.67,0:28:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要小心点 别干预别人家的事\N{\reng}We ought to be careful, messing in folk business.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.94,0:28:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,圣经中可没有这样说\N{\reng}It don't say that in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.97,0:28:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“要小心”\N{\reng}"Be careful."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.20,0:28:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“国王将回答他们说\N{\reng}"And the King shall answer and say unto them,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.52,0:28:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我实实在在告诉你们 你们既然\N{\reng}verily I say unto thee, inasmuch as ye hath done it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.70,0:28:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,对这些人中最小的下手 也就是向我下手"\N{\reng}unto the least of these, my brethren, ye have done it unto me."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.87,0:28:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 梅布尔\N{\reng}All right, Mabel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.97,0:28:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,不要说什么“要小心”\N{\reng}Don't say about "be careful."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.57,0:28:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,来量一量\N{\reng}Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.35,0:28:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,一 二 三 就这样\N{\reng}One, two, three. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.67,0:29:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,这些是梅布尔女士送的\N{\reng}They're from Miss Mabel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.15,0:29:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,北卡罗来纳州巴克利县的凯瑟琳·丹妮尔·克拉克\N{\reng}Catherine Danielle Clark, of Barkley County, North Carolina,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.22,0:29:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,被指控对原巴克利湾的\N{\reng}is charged with the murder in the first degree
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.80,0:29:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,蔡斯·劳伦斯·安德鲁斯\N{\reng}of Chase Lawrence Andrews,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.48,0:29:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,实施了一级谋杀\N{\reng}formerly of Barkley Cove.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.10,0:29:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,在这种情况下 控方可以要求判处死刑\N{\reng}In such cases, the State is allowed to seek the death penalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.87,0:29:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,控方已经宣布如果被告\N{\reng}The prosecution has announced it will do so
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.95,0:29:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,被定罪就将这么做\N{\reng}if the defendant is found guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.77,0:29:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,有罪 我们都知道她有罪\N{\reng}Guilty! We all know she's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.45,0:29:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,她有罪\N{\reng}She's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.52,0:29:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在将开始选择陪审团\N{\reng}We will now begin jury selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.52,0:29:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的准陪审员是不是在前两排...\N{\reng}Will our prospective jurors in the first two rows...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.82,0:29:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,有一个选择 就是所谓的辩诉交易\N{\reng}There is an option. It's what's called a plea bargain.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.20,0:30:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着 如果你愿意承认\N{\reng}And it means that if you are willing to say
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.63,0:30:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你那晚确实去了消防塔见了蔡斯·安德鲁斯\N{\reng}that you did go to the tower that night and met Chase Andrews there
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.45,0:30:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,然后你们发生争执 在一次可怕的意外中\N{\reng}and you had a disagreement, and in a horrible accident
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.20,0:30:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他向后退了一步 掉出了栅栏\N{\reng}he stepped backwards through the grate,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.75,0:30:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你会被判十年 但你会在六年内出狱\N{\reng}you'd get ten years, but you'd be out in six.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.75,0:30:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\reng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.17,0:30:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们输了 会输得很惨\N{\reng}If we lose, we lose big.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.32,0:30:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,是终身监禁 或更重\N{\reng}It's life in prison, or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.52,0:30:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,米尔顿先生 我不会说任何暗示有罪的话\N{\reng}Mr. Milton, I won't say anything that implies guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.20,0:30:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会坐牢\N{\reng}I will not go to prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.02,0:30:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,请叫我汤姆\N{\reng}Please call me Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.55,0:30:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,答应我 你会考虑这个建议\N{\reng}And promise me that you will think about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.45,0:30:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须离开这里\N{\reng}I have to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.57,0:30:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,无论...\N{\reng}One way...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.67,0:30:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,如何\N{\reng}or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.55,0:30:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在10月30日午夜至凌晨2点之间...\N{\reng}Between midnight and 2 a.m. on October 30th...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.50,0:30:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,被告将蔡斯·安德鲁引诱到塔楼上 并将其推下摔死\N{\reng}the defendant lured Chase Andrews to the tower and pushed him to his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.27,0:30:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,然后她抹掉了她的足迹和指纹\N{\reng}She then covered up her tracks and fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.92,0:31:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,现在 你们会听到她有时间 她有动机\N{\reng}Now, you're gonna hear she had the time, she had the motivation,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.22,0:31:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但最重要的是...\N{\reng}but most importantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.25,0:31:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,她有性格缺陷去谋杀蔡斯·安德鲁斯\N{\reng}she has the weakness of character to murder Chase Andrews.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.84,0:31:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs17\pos(192,276)\c&HF6F6F6&\1a&H23&}保持冷静
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.10,0:31:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们 先生们 公诉方将向你们抛出许多有关\N{\reng}Ladies and gentlemen, the State is going to throw a lot of words at you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.52,0:31:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳·丹妮尔·克拉克小姐的说法\N{\reng}about Miss Catherine Danielle Clark.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.90,0:31:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但我请求你们看看\N{\reng}But I am asking you to look at the evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.00,0:31:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,公诉方将提供支持这些说法的证据\N{\reng}that the State will be offering to back up those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.40,0:31:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你们会发现并没有\N{\reng}You'll find that there is none.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.05,0:31:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,此外 你们会发现很可能\N{\reng}Furthermore, you are going to hear that there's a good chance
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.17,0:31:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人谋杀蔡斯·安德鲁斯 被告克拉克小姐\N{\reng}no one murdered Chase Andrews and that the defendant, Miss Clark,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.87,0:31:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,之所以在这里 是因为把责任归咎于一个局外人\N{\reng}finds herself here because it is easier to lay blame on an outsider
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.42,0:31:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,比依靠事实更简单\N{\reng}than it is to rely on facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.55,0:31:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管她在离这个法庭不到五英里的地方出生和长大\N{\reng}And although she was born and grew up not five miles from this courtroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.50,0:32:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,克拉克小姐正是个局外人\N{\reng}Miss Clark is an outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.70,0:33:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs17\pos(192,276)\c&HF6F6F6&\1a&H23&}火花塞
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.75,0:33:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,噢\N{\reng}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.47,0:34:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\reng}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.07,0:34:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,是我 泰特\N{\reng}It's me. Tate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.75,0:34:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,苔原天鹅\N{\reng}Tundra swan.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.45,0:34:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你怎么会了解鸟?  - 我妈妈喜欢鸟\N{\reng}- How do you know birds?  - My ma liked birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.90,0:34:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我看不懂你的字条\N{\reng}I can't read your note.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.97,0:34:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 字条是说我在外面钓鱼时见过你几次\N{\reng}Oh, all I said was I'd seen you a couple times when I was out fishing,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.32,0:34:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这让我想到 也许你需要一些种子和一个火花塞\N{\reng}and it got me thinking that maybe you could use some seeds and a spark plug.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.27,0:34:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我有多余的 我想这会节省你去镇上的时间\N{\reng}I had extra. Thought it might save you a trip to town.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.75,0:34:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,呃 我也不清楚 但我想你会喜欢这些羽毛\N{\reng}And, uh, I don't know, I figured you'd like the feathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.22,0:35:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,那好吧\N{\reng}All right, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.17,0:35:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那好吧\N{\reng}All right, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.27,0:35:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 我最好走了 所以...\N{\reng}Well, I better be going, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.05,0:35:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以教你认字\N{\reng}I could teach you to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.07,0:35:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你不妨同时学习书写\N{\reng}I thought you may as well learn to write at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.65,0:35:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 好的\N{\reng}Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.22,0:35:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,很好 好 那么我们从A开始\N{\reng}Good. Okay, so we start with A.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.05,0:35:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,请在这里描出它的形状\N{\reng}Just go ahead and draw that shape right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.45,0:35:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,别告诉我\N{\reng}Don't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.27,0:35:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你快做到了\N{\reng}You're getting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.57,0:35:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 别提示我  - 当然 我有一整天时间\N{\reng}- Don't help me.  - Sure. I got all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.92,0:36:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“有些人可以不靠\N{\reng}"There are some who can live
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.57,0:36:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,野外的东西生活 逗号\N{\reng}without wild things, comma,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.42,0:36:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,有些人则不能”\N{\reng}and some who cannot."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.79,0:36:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我所说的 凯雅 哇\N{\reng}That's what I'm talking about, Kya. Whoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.32,0:36:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,而且再也不会有不能读的时候了 永远不会\N{\reng}And there will never be a time again where you can't read, ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.35,0:36:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道文字可以这么丰富\N{\reng}I didn't know words could hold so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.82,0:36:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,不是所有文字都丰富\N{\reng}Not all words hold that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.52,0:36:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以找个时间在我家读书\N{\reng}We could read at my house sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.52,0:37:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们翻遍了所有的藏书\N{\reng\i1}We went through the whole library.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.87,0:37:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}从夏天到秋天 每周三次\N{\reng\i1}Three times a week, summer into fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.77,0:37:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}阅读植物和动物如何随时间改变\N{\reng\i1}Read how plants and animals change over time
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.22,0:37:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以适应不断变化的环境\N{\reng\i1}to adjust to the ever-shifting earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.36,0:37:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs17\pos(192,276)\c&HF6F6F6&\1a&H23&}生物学
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.20,0:37:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}鸟儿大多在黎明时分鸣唱 因为早晨凉爽湿润的空气\N{\reng\i1}How birds sing mostly at dawn because the cool, moist air of morning
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.25,0:37:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}会将它们的鸣唱及含义带得更远\N{\reng\i1}carries their songs and their meanings much farther.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.17,0:37:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一些细胞如何分裂并特化为肺或心脏\N{\reng\i1}How some cells divide and specialize into lungs or hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.57,0:37:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}而其它的则作为干细胞维持原状\N{\reng\i1}while others remain uncommitted as stem cells
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.47,0:37:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以备后来之需\N{\reng\i1}in case they're needed later.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.75,0:37:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在所有生物学的世界里...\N{\reng\i1}Within all the worlds of biology...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.32,0:37:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我在寻找一个解释 为什么一个母亲会抛下她的后代\N{\reng\i1}I searched for an explanation of why a mother would leave her offspring.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.80,0:37:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“杰克逊·亨利·克拉克先生\N{\reng}"Mr. Jackson Henry Clark
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.35,0:37:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,在1933年6月12日与朱利安·玛丽亚·雅克小姐结婚”\N{\reng}married Miss Julienne Maria Jacques, June 12, 1933."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.30,0:38:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,这说明这些是我的父母\N{\reng}That means these are my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.35,0:38:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“杰里米·安德鲁·克拉克先生 1月2日”\N{\reng}"Master Jeremy Andrew Clark, January 2."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.17,0:38:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,那是朱迪\N{\reng}That's Jodie.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.95,0:38:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“纳皮尔·墨菲·克拉克先生 玛丽·海伦·克拉克小姐\N{\reng}"Master Napier Murphy Clark, Miss Mary Helen Clark,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.54,0:38:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳·丹妮尔·克拉克小姐”\N{\reng}Miss Catherine Danielle Clark."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.15,0:38:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我想念他们\N{\reng}I miss them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.37,0:38:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我 呃...\N{\reng}I had, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.92,0:38:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经忘了他们...\N{\reng}I had forgot how much...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.95,0:38:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,离开这里有多久了\N{\reng}I feel them not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.15,0:38:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,但是...\N{\reng}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.27,0:38:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在感觉不到他们在这里\N{\reng}I feel them not here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.05,0:38:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说...\N{\reng}I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.80,0:38:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,有时我觉得自己太不显眼...\N{\reng}Sometimes I feel so invisible...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.57,0:38:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我想知道我是否真的在这里\N{\reng}I wonder if I'm here at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.60,0:38:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你在\N{\reng}You are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.45,0:39:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- 抱歉 我迟到了  - 来吧 帮我一把\N{\reng}- Sorry I'm late.  - Come on. Give me a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.22,0:39:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,儿子 你知道我不听闲言碎语\N{\reng}Son, you know I don't listen to idle talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.70,0:39:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但有个频繁的流言在到处传播\N{\reng}But there is a regular riptide of gossip going around
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.45,0:39:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你和那个沼泽女孩的一些事\N{\reng}you got something going on with that Marsh Girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.20,0:39:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道你可以告诉我任何事\N{\reng}Hey, you know you can tell me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.77,0:39:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- 她是你女朋友吗?  - 她是我朋友\N{\reng}- She your girlfriend?  - She's my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.80,0:39:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我给她带书去 因为大家很讨厌她 她无法去上学\N{\reng}I bring her books 'cause people are so nasty to her, she can't go to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.25,0:39:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,她没有任何家人\N{\reng}She doesn't have any family.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.27,0:39:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 拜托 没必要发火\N{\reng}Hey. Come on. There's no need to be huffy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.35,0:39:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我的任务是说出所有我们不喜欢提及的事\N{\reng}It's my job to say all the things that we don't like to talk about,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.42,0:39:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我没法给你很多其他爸爸能给他们儿子的东西\N{\reng}and I can't give you a lot of things those other dads can give their sons.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.97,0:39:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我才问你\N{\reng}So I'm asking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.12,0:39:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,只是注意点\N{\reng}Just be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.22,0:39:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你为之努力的一切 你上教堂山分校的梦想...\N{\reng}Everything you've worked so hard for, your dreams of going to Chapel Hill...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.45,0:39:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,人生可以在瞬间改变\N{\reng}Life can change in a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.65,0:40:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你明白吗?\N{\reng}You understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.57,0:40:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,明白\N{\reng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.95,0:40:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,去把音乐音量调高点好吗? 去吧\N{\reng}Now turn up my music, would you? Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.52,0:40:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,顺便说下 是普契尼的作品\N{\reng}It's Puccini, in case you're wondering.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.47,0:40:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,一个年轻女孩这样独自生活看起来很不道德 你不觉得吗?\N{\reng}A young girl living on her own like that looks immoral, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.15,0:40:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,不 先生 我不这么认为\N{\reng}No, sir. I don't. Think, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.30,0:40:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,没到那种程度 可以问问我妻子\N{\reng}At least not enough. Just ask my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.65,0:40:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,有一些不错的集体之家\N{\reng}There are some fine group homes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.12,0:40:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,可以帮助一个年轻女子避免麻烦\N{\reng}that would help keep a young woman out of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.65,0:40:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他们说她时常来这里\N{\reng}They say she comes in here from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.32,0:40:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我确实经常见到她\N{\reng}I do see her from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.15,0:41:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,她不是一个人 她和她父亲一起\N{\reng}She's not alone. She's got her father with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.65,0:41:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 这么久以来 我都从未见过她家有其他人\N{\reng}Well, I've never seen anybody home all the times I've been by.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.47,0:41:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,她一般什么时候来?\N{\reng}When does she usually come around?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.50,0:41:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道她什么时候会来\N{\reng}I never know just when she'll boat in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.05,0:41:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,她下次来的时候给我打电话\N{\reng}Have her call me next time she comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.27,0:41:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你没有任何理由骗我 是吗 伙计?\N{\reng}You don't have any reason to lie to me, do you, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.57,0:41:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,完全没有 先生\N{\reng}No reason at all, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.80,0:41:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们得在别的地方见面  - 嗨 凯雅 也很高兴见到你\N{\reng}- We gotta meet somewhere else.  - Hi, Kya. Good to see you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.90,0:41:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,社会服务部门又在找我了\N{\reng}Social Services are looking for me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.70,0:41:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会把我弄走 把我送到某个集体之家\N{\reng}They're gonna pull me in, put me in some group home.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.00,0:41:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,见到人打招呼是有礼貌的表现\N{\reng}It's polite to greet people when you see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.60,0:41:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 集体之家可能不是最糟的\N{\reng}You know, a group home might not be the worst thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.72,0:42:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,什么? 不 不 有人会给你做暖和的饭菜\N{\reng}What? No, no. You'd have someone cooking you warm meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.85,0:42:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- 真正的床  - 我有一张真正的床\N{\reng}- Real bed.  - I got a real bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.72,0:42:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,毕竟 我永远不会离开沼泽地去和一群陌生人生活\N{\reng}'Sides, I'd never leave the marsh to go live with a bunch of strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.06,0:42:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,是“况且” 不是“毕竟”\N{\reng}It's "besides," not "'sides."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.37,0:42:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你不可能永远独自生活在沼泽里\N{\reng}And you can't live alone in the marsh forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.05,0:42:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,等着瞧\N{\reng}Watch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.65,0:42:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\reng}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.80,0:42:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,泰特\N{\reng}Tate.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.20,0:42:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我 呃...\N{\reng}I, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.92,0:42:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我感谢你教我阅读\N{\reng}I appreciate you teaching me to read
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.51,0:42:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,以及你给我的所有东西\N{\reng}and all the things you gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.85,0:42:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但你为啥要这么做呢?\N{\reng}But why do you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.94,0:42:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你没有女朋友或其它事吗?\N{\reng}Don't you have a girlfriend or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.67,0:42:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,有时我会这么做\N{\reng}Sometimes I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.61,0:42:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,有时?\N{\reng}Sometimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.78,0:42:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 我已经有一个\N{\reng}I mean, I've had one.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.99,0:43:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,呃 但不是现在...\N{\reng}Uh, but not now...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.65,0:43:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我也不知道 所以...\N{\reng}I don't, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.37,0:43:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,呃 好吧\N{\reng}Uh, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.95,0:43:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我 呃...\N{\reng}I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.60,0:43:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,前几天我在你爸爸的船上看到你了\N{\reng}I saw you on your pa's boat the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.42,0:43:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,他看起来真好 你爸爸\N{\reng}He seems real nice, your dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.97,0:43:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 他是很好\N{\reng}Yeah. Yeah, he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.62,0:43:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,你从不提到你的母亲\N{\reng}You never talk about your ma.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.64,0:43:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,她是什么样的人?\N{\reng}What's she like?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.61,0:43:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,呃 你什么都不用说\N{\reng}Uh, you don't have to say nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.62,0:43:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我母亲和小妹在阿什维尔的一场车祸中死了\N{\reng}My mother and little sister died in a car wreck over in Asheville.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.20,0:43:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我小妹的名字是卡莉安\N{\reng}My little sister's name was Carianne.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.57,0:43:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,那是 呃...\N{\reng}It was, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.30,0:43:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,什么 泰特?\N{\reng}What, Tate?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.00,0:44:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以对我说任何事\N{\reng}You can say anything to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.60,0:44:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我想她们去阿什维尔是为了给我买生日礼物\N{\reng}I think they went to Asheville to buy me my birthday present.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.48,0:44:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,一辆我想要的脚踏车\N{\reng}There was this bike I wanted,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.55,0:44:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,西部汽车公司没有卖的...\N{\reng}and Western Auto didn't carry it...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.15,0:44:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我想她们去阿什维尔是为我买脚踏车\N{\reng}so I think they went into Asheville to get that bike for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.80,0:44:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,噢\N{\reng}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.80,0:44:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我甚至都不记得那是什么脚踏车了\N{\reng}And I don't even remember what kind of bike it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.50,0:44:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是你的错\N{\reng}It wasn't your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.62,0:44:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,噢\N{\reng}Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.77,0:44:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 我的天\N{\reng}Oh, my gosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.37,0:45:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在是你女朋友吗?\N{\reng}Am I your girlfriend now?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.15,0:45:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你想成为吗?\N{\reng}Do you wanna be?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.20,0:45:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我了解羽毛\N{\reng}I know feathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.20,0:45:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我肯定其他女孩不认识羽毛\N{\reng}Bet the other girls don't know feathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.45,0:45:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,那好吧\N{\reng}All right, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.76,0:45:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那好吧\N{\reng}All right, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.47,0:46:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我从来没有走过这条路  - 这值得一游\N{\reng}- I've never been out this way.  - It's worth the trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.82,0:46:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你会看到\N{\reng}You'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.12,0:46:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,生日快乐 凯雅\N{\reng}Happy birthday, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.57,0:46:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道今天是我生日?\N{\reng}How'd you know it was my birthday?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.32,0:46:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我在你的圣经中读到过\N{\reng}Oh, I read it in your Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.25,0:46:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道今天是你的生日吗?\N{\reng}Did you know it was your birthday?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.40,0:47:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有日历\N{\reng}Don't have a calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.70,0:47:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 不是我的名字\N{\reng}Oh, um, not my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.60,0:47:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,不要切我的名字\N{\reng}Don't cut my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.82,0:47:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,遵命 女士\N{\reng}Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.83,0:47:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗯  - 很好吃 是吧?\N{\reng}- Mm!  - Pretty good, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.13,0:47:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,那是什么?\N{\reng}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.40,0:47:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,它们来了\N{\reng}Here they come.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.62,0:47:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 哇\N{\reng}Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.98,0:47:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,雪雁\N{\reng}Snow geese.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.95,0:48:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.27,0:48:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 看着我\N{\reng}Kya, look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.30,0:49:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.19,0:49:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 很抱歉\N{\reng}Kya, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.03,0:49:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,很抱歉\N{\reng}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.70,0:49:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,天哪\N{\reng}Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.37,0:49:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不 泰特 我想要\N{\reng}No, Tate, I want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.82,0:49:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不呢?\N{\reng}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.30,0:49:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我...\N{\reng}Because I...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.40,0:49:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我太在乎你了\N{\reng}I care about you too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.88,0:49:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 凯雅 我想要你胜过一切 但我不能让你受伤害\N{\reng}Look, Kya. I want you more than anything, but I can't be damaged as easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.12,0:49:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,这对你来说更危险 你明白吗?\N{\reng}It's more dangerous for you. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.07,0:49:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}秋天让位给了冬天\N{\reng\i1}Fall gave way to winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.62,0:49:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}冬天到春天\N{\reng\i1}Winter to spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.41,0:50:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}自然界中唯一不变的就是变化\N{\reng\i1}The only constant in nature is change.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.33,0:50:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸 我被录取了\N{\reng}Dad, I got in!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.18,0:50:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么不说话?\N{\reng}Why are you quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.42,0:50:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我很快就要离开了\N{\reng}You know I'm going away soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.05,0:50:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,上大学\N{\reng}To college.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.40,0:50:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你说过这个\N{\reng}You talked about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.74,0:50:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,啥时候?\N{\reng}When?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.90,0:50:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,不是马上去\N{\reng}Not right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.15,0:50:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,快了\N{\reng}Soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.57,0:50:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我在生物实验室找到份工作\N{\reng}I got a job at the biology lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.21,0:50:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,下周上班 所以...\N{\reng}Starts next week, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.65,0:51:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,留下\N{\reng}Stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.56,0:51:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,然后做什么?\N{\reng}And do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.52,0:51:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,不 听着 我只是说这里没有适合我的工作\N{\reng}No, look. I just mean there's no work for me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.87,0:51:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我要做什么? 我不想成为像我爸爸那样的渔夫\N{\reng}What am I gonna do? I don't want to be a shrimper like my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.28,0:51:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我会拿到学位并有所作为 凯雅\N{\reng}I'm going to get a degree and be something, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.25,0:51:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你也可以  - 你想让我成为什么?\N{\reng}- So could you.  - What do you want me to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.20,0:51:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我不是这个意思  - 你永远不会回来了\N{\reng}- That's not what I meant.  - You're never gonna come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.87,0:51:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我会回来 我不会离开你 凯雅 我保证\N{\reng}Yes, I will. I won't leave you, Kya. I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.91,0:51:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我会回来找你\N{\reng}I'm gonna come back to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.29,0:51:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 停下 凯...\N{\reng}Kya! Kya, stop! Ky...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.20,0:51:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能逃避每一个问题\N{\reng}You can't run away from every whip stitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.42,0:51:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 再多一晚  - 再多一晚\N{\reng}- One more night.  - One more night.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.22,0:52:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么?\N{\reng}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.52,0:52:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,是一份出版商名单\N{\reng}It's a list of publishers.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.60,0:52:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,为你所有的图纸和笔记\N{\reng}For all your drawings and notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.57,0:52:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,外面没有这类东西 凯雅\N{\reng}There's nothing like them out there, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.25,0:52:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,这足够写本书了\N{\reng}There's enough for a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.15,0:52:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,很多书\N{\reng}Lots of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.92,0:52:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,还有 知道吗 你不必离开家\N{\reng}And, you know, you wouldn't have to leave home.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.80,0:52:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以直接将你的样稿寄给出版商\N{\reng}You could just mail your samples into a publisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.92,0:52:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 可以挣点钱\N{\reng}You know, bring some money in.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.85,0:52:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你也知道可能不会挣大钱...\N{\reng}You know, probably not a huge amount...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.25,0:52:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但你也不用在以后的日子里挖贻贝了\N{\reng}but maybe you wouldn't have to dig mussels the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.05,0:52:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,试试吧 凯雅\N{\reng}Just give it a try, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.60,0:53:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托 这有什么损失呢?\N{\reng}Come on. What can it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.62,0:53:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你会忘记我的\N{\reng}You're gonna forget about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.82,0:53:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,当你忙于大学那些事情时\N{\reng}When you get busy with all that college stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.75,0:53:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,那些漂亮的女孩\N{\reng}all those pretty girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.97,0:53:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我永远不会忘记你 凯雅\N{\reng}I could never forget you, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.56,0:53:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,永远\N{\reng}Ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.98,0:53:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我会在一个月内回家 我保证 在独立日 好吗?\N{\reng}I'll be home in a month. I promise. For the Fourth of July. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.70,0:53:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我会在你了解这事之前回来\N{\reng}I'll be back before you know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.97,0:53:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会在你的海滩上见面 一起看烟花\N{\reng}We'll meet on your beach and watch fireworks together.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.04,0:53:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,一定记下这些出版商 好吗?\N{\reng}Just write those publishers, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.80,0:53:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,再见 凯雅\N{\reng}Goodbye, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.05,0:53:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,再见 泰特\N{\reng}Goodbye, Tate.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.27,0:54:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,东海岸的海鸟\N{\reng}Seabirds of the Eastern Seaboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.76,0:54:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你是主演 大红\N{\reng}Starring you, Big Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.72,0:56:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\reng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.30,0:56:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\reng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.10,0:56:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,不 泰特\N{\reng}No, Tate.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.55,0:56:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不\N{\reng}No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.57,0:56:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\reng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.86,0:56:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\reng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.53,0:56:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\reng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.52,0:56:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不 不\N{\reng}No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.60,0:57:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}泰特和生活以及爱情一直是同一件事\N{\reng\i1}Tate and life and love had been the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.25,0:57:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们都消失了\N{\reng\i1}They were all gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.06,0:57:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然后...\N{\reng\i1}And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.77,0:57:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每当我受伤时 沼泽都会抚慰我\N{\reng\i1}Whenever I stumbled, the marsh caught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.18,0:57:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在不知不觉间\N{\reng\i1}At some unclaimed moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.93,0:58:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最后 心痛的感觉就像\N{\reng\i1}at last, the heart pain seeped away,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.75,0:58:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}水入沙般消散了\N{\reng\i1}like water into sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.52,0:58:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它仍在 但在内心深处\N{\reng\i1}Still there, but deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.57,0:58:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,尸体周围和消防塔上都没有脚印\N{\reng}There were no footprints around the body or on the fire tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.15,0:58:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,也没有新鲜的指纹\N{\reng}And no fresh fingerprints either.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.11,0:58:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至在栅栏上也没有 但肯定有人打开了它\N{\reng}Not even on the grate, which somebody had to open.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.07,0:58:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,所有这些都表明 有人破坏了证据\N{\reng}All this indicated that someone had destroyed evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.67,0:58:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,没有问题了\N{\reng}No more questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.62,0:58:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你的证词\N{\reng}Your witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.50,0:58:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,警长 我把10月29日晚上\N{\reng}Sheriff, I'm handing you the tide table
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.17,0:58:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,和10月30日上午的潮汐表交给你了\N{\reng}for the night of October 29 and the morning of October 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.00,0:58:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,现在 这表明这里的低潮是在午夜左右\N{\reng}Now, this shows here that low tide was around midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.77,0:58:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 在蔡斯·安德鲁斯到达消防塔\N{\reng}So at the time Chase Andrews arrived at the tower
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.80,0:58:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,并走到台阶上时 就会在湿泥中留下足迹\N{\reng}and walked to the steps, he would have made tracks in the wet mud.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.86,0:58:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,然后随着地下水位的上升 这些足迹就会被冲掉\N{\reng}And then as the groundwater rose, those tracks would have been wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.25,0:58:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你同意有这个可能吗?  - 嗯...\N{\reng}- Do you agree that this is possible?  - Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.12,0:59:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,然后你会同意 如果他有任何朋友和他在一起\N{\reng}And then you'd agree that if he had any friends with him,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.77,0:59:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他们的脚印也会被冲掉\N{\reng}their footprints would be washed away as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.79,0:59:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在这种情况下\N{\reng}Under these circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.17,0:59:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,没有脚印本身并不表明是犯罪\N{\reng}the absence of footprints in and of itself does not suggest a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.92,0:59:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,对吗?\N{\reng}Correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.97,0:59:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,警长?\N{\reng}Sheriff?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.47,0:59:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,没有脚印本身并不能证明存在犯罪\N{\reng}The absence of footprints does not, by itself, prove there was a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.57,0:59:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你还作证说在消防塔的任何地方\N{\reng}You also testified that there were no fingerprints
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.60,0:59:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,包括在敞开的炉架上 都没有发现指纹\N{\reng}found anywhere in the fire tower, including on the open grate.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.50,0:59:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 这使你得出结论 肯定是有人打开了栅栏\N{\reng}So this led you to conclude that someone must have opened the grate
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.80,0:59:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,并在事后擦掉了他们的指纹\N{\reng}and wiped away their fingerprints afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.40,0:59:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,对\N{\reng}Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.33,0:59:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上 这些栅栏是不是经常被打开\N{\reng}Now, in fact, isn't it true that these grates were left open
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.10,0:59:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,并被认为是非常危险的\N{\reng}so often and considered so dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.84,0:59:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,以至于你的办公室在去年7月18日\N{\reng}that your office submitted a written request
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.67,0:59:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,向美国森林服务局\N{\reng}to the U.S. Forest Service
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.26,1:00:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,提交了一份书面请求要求纠正该情况?\N{\reng}to remedy the situation on July 18 of last year?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.37,1:00:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,这是该请求的副本\N{\reng}This is a copy of that request.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.98,1:00:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,这是谁写的 警长?\N{\reng}Who wrote this, sheriff?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.85,1:00:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我自己写的\N{\reng}I did it myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.17,1:00:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你能向法庭宣读你提交给森林局\N{\reng}Would you read to the court the last sentence of this document
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.74,1:00:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,这份文件的最后一段话吗?\N{\reng}that you sent to the Forest Service?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.55,1:00:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,只是最后一段话\N{\reng}Just the last sentence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.82,1:00:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“我必须重复一遍 这些栅栏非常危险\N{\reng}"I must repeat, these grates are very dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.66,1:00:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,如果不采取行动...\N{\reng}and if action is not taken...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.65,1:00:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,将发生严重的伤害或死亡”\N{\reng}If action is not taken, a serious injury or death will occur."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.82,1:00:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 警长\N{\reng}Thank you, sheriff.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.12,1:01:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,有人在我的房子周围拍照\N{\reng}Somebody's been taking pictures round my house.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.95,1:01:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你觉得他们想干什么?\N{\reng}What do you think they want?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.30,1:01:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,开发商\N{\reng}Developers.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.48,1:01:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,过去几周 他们一直在沼泽地里进进出出\N{\reng}They've been all up and down the marsh last few weeks,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.37,1:01:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,想把“浊水沼泽”排干 建造酒店\N{\reng}wanting to drain the "murky swamp." Build hotels.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.25,1:01:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,对 我去年见过他们\N{\reng}Yeah, I saw them last year.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.36,1:01:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,砍伐橡木 并在下面的路上挖渠道\N{\reng}Cutting oak and digging channels down the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.12,1:01:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他们想要我的房子?\N{\reng}They want my house?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.22,1:01:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,也许不是房子\N{\reng}Maybe not the house,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.65,1:01:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但我肯定他们会为那块地给你一大笔钱\N{\reng}but I bet they offer you a heap of money for that land.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.79,1:01:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,朱姆平\N{\reng}Jumpin'!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.87,1:01:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,给凯雅一笔钱并没有什么不好\N{\reng}There ain't nothing wrong with some money going to Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.00,1:01:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你确实拥有那块地吗? 你拥有那所房子?\N{\reng}You do own that land, don't you? You own that house?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.22,1:02:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸说是这样\N{\reng}Pa said so.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.65,1:02:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,那么 你需要一些证据\N{\reng}Well, you're gonna need some proof.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.62,1:02:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,契约 所有权\N{\reng}A deed, title.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.47,1:02:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\reng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.52,1:02:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉吓到你了 我可以帮你拿吗?\N{\reng}Sorry to startle you. Can I carry that for ya?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.98,1:02:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我拿着  - 请让我来拿\N{\reng}- I got it.  - Please. Let me get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.47,1:02:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 我是蔡斯·安德鲁斯\N{\reng}Oh, I'm Chase Andrews.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.36,1:02:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你叫凯雅 对吗?\N{\reng}Your name's Kya, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.57,1:02:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个好名字 我喜欢 它与众不同而且很好\N{\reng}Yeah. Yeah. It's a nice name. I like it. It's different but nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.20,1:02:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是你的船\N{\reng}This is yours right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.35,1:02:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,好了\N{\reng}There we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.25,1:02:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这周日你想去我的船上野餐吗?\N{\reng}You wanna go for a picnic in my boat this Sunday?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.25,1:02:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,好\N{\reng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.10,1:02:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,中午我去尖峰海滩接你 这样行吗?\N{\reng}I'll pick you up at noon from Point Beach. Does that work?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.18,1:02:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 好吧 再见 凯雅\N{\reng}All right. Well, I'll see ya, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.95,1:03:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 我们到了\N{\reng}Well, here we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.27,1:03:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,纳皮尔·克拉克先生 看来在1897年买了它\N{\reng}Mr. Napier Clark, looks like, bought it in 1897.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.95,1:03:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 呃 那是我爷爷\N{\reng}Yeah, uh, that's my grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.10,1:03:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 女士\N{\reng}Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.79,1:03:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它从未被出售过 确实 我想它是属于你的\N{\reng}It's never been sold, so, yes sirree, I reckon it belongs to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.42,1:03:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,看来如果你想保有它就得补交一些税 克拉克小姐\N{\reng}Looks like you gotta pay some back taxes if you wanna keep it, Miss Clark.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.68,1:03:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上 女士 按照法律的规定\N{\reng}In fact, ma'am, the way the law reads, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.05,1:03:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,谁出来并支付这些补缴的税款谁就拥有土地\N{\reng}whoever comes along and pays those back taxes owns the land,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.87,1:03:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,即使他们没有任何契约\N{\reng}even if they don't got no deed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.50,1:03:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,那要多少钱?\N{\reng}Well, how much?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.72,1:03:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,看起来是...\N{\reng}Looks like about...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.10,1:03:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,总共八百美元\N{\reng}Eight hundred dollars total.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.37,1:04:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}五年\N{\reng\i1}Five years.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.07,1:04:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}自从泰特给我看这条路以来 已经有五年了\N{\reng\i1}It had been five years since Tate showed me this path.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.14,1:04:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}亲爱的先生或女士\N{\reng\i1}Dear Sir or Madam,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.82,1:04:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我给你寄去几页关于卡罗莱纳沼泽地的贝壳资料\N{\reng\i1}I am sending you the following pages on the shells of the Carolina marsh
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.10,1:04:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}供您参考\N{\reng\i1}for your consideration.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.50,1:04:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}五年来 我再次打开了心扉\N{\reng\i1}Five years for my heart to open its shell again.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.00,1:04:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,沉浸在音乐天才面前的感觉如何?\N{\reng}How's it feel to bask in the presence of musical genius?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.90,1:04:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 看\N{\reng}Hey, look.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.35,1:04:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 噢 这是个栉孔扇贝\N{\reng}Oh. Oh! That's an ornate scallop.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.25,1:04:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,梳饰扇贝\N{\reng}Pecten ornatus.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.62,1:04:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\reng}All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.10,1:05:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- 在这里发现一个很难得  - 真的吗?\N{\reng}- Well, it's unusual to find one here.  - Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.02,1:05:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 这个特殊物种一般生活在这里以南的地区\N{\reng}Yeah. This particular species usually inhabits regions south of here
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.40,1:05:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这里的水对它们来说太冷了\N{\reng}'cause these waters are too cool for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.60,1:05:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了?\N{\reng}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.15,1:05:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,没什么 只是 沼泽女孩知道贝壳的拉丁文名称\N{\reng}Oh, no, it's just, the Marsh Girl knows the Latin name for shells
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.87,1:05:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,以及它们生活的地方和原因 我的天哪\N{\reng}and where they inhabit and why, for Christ sakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.07,1:05:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,给 你留着吧\N{\reng}Here. You keep it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.13,1:05:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\reng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.40,1:05:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是与众不同 不是吗?\N{\reng}You're something else, ain't ya?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.28,1:06:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你认为我没用 但我比一次野餐更有价值\N{\reng}I know you think I'm trash, but I'm worth more than a picnic.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.95,1:06:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 不 凯雅 拜托\N{\reng}Oh, no, Kya. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.29,1:06:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,很抱歉 拜托 我从来没有觉得你没用\N{\reng}I'm sorry. No. Hey, come on. I've never thought you were trash.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.42,1:06:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,求你了 对不起\N{\reng}Please. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.59,1:06:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想走 我理解 但你也没法走啊\N{\reng}I understand if you wanna go, but you can't walk from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.87,1:06:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,太远了\N{\reng}It's too far.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.30,1:06:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以弥补吗?\N{\reng}Can I make it up to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.47,1:06:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托 我可以弥补吗?\N{\reng}Please, can I make it up to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.93,1:06:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我不信你从没有上过消防塔\N{\reng}I can't believe you never been up the fire tower.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.32,1:06:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,当我父母烦我的时候我就来这里 你知道吗?\N{\reng}Come here when my family's all in my business. You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.15,1:06:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个从上面看整个沼泽的好方法\N{\reng}It's a great way to see the whole marsh from above.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.99,1:06:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,来\N{\reng}Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.43,1:07:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,它是什么?\N{\reng}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.47,1:07:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以说 我不会笑话你\N{\reng}You can tell me. I won't laugh at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.81,1:07:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,它就像你有个一生的朋友 但你从未见过它的全貌\N{\reng}It's like having a friend your whole life, but you never saw their full face.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.30,1:07:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我看到了\N{\reng}Now I see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.40,1:07:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你的房子在那边 是吗?\N{\reng}Your house is over there, ain't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.58,1:07:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,带我去那里\N{\reng}Take me there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.38,1:07:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 呃...\N{\reng}Oh, um...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.55,1:07:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 它很远  - 嘿 我喜欢远\N{\reng}- It's far.  - Hey, I like far.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.67,1:07:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我不在乎它是什么样子 如果你担心这个的话\N{\reng}I don't care what it's like, if that's what you're worried about.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.10,1:07:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这里了吗?\N{\reng}Is this it right here?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.52,1:07:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你一个人在这里住多久了?\N{\reng}How long you lived out here by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.78,1:07:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,呃 我想大概十年了\N{\reng}Uh, about ten years, I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.53,1:07:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,很整洁\N{\reng}Neat.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.20,1:08:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,在这里生活 没有父母指点该怎么做?\N{\reng}Living out here with no parents telling you what to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.45,1:08:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,里面真的没什么可看的\N{\reng}There's really nothing to see inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.87,1:08:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- 哇 你的门廊上有什么?  - 什么?\N{\reng}- Wow, what you got on the porch?  - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.50,1:08:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 呃 没什么\N{\reng}Oh, um, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.27,1:08:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这都是些什么?\N{\reng}What is all this?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.85,1:08:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,没什么\N{\reng}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.40,1:08:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,什么 你在写书还是什么的?\N{\reng}What, you writing a book or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.30,1:08:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,算是吧\N{\reng}Sort of.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.49,1:08:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这些看起来直接来自百科全书\N{\reng}These look straight out of an encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.97,1:08:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你是原创者 不是吗?\N{\reng}You're the real deal, ain't ya?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.42,1:08:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,啊 天鹅绒\N{\reng}Ah, swanee.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.10,1:08:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你有个水泵\N{\reng}You got a water pump.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.80,1:08:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我还没准备好接待客人\N{\reng}I wasn't ready for guests.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.37,1:09:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 别担心\N{\reng}Hey, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.22,1:09:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 我知道没有人可以像这样独自在这里生活\N{\reng}Hey, there's nobody I know who could live out here alone like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.02,1:09:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 大多数人都会很害怕\N{\reng}I mean, most guys would be too scared.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.69,1:09:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你想从我这里得到什么?\N{\reng}What do you want with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.82,1:09:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 听着 我真的很抱歉说这些\N{\reng}Okay. Look, I'm real sorry I came on like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.62,1:09:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我想更好的了解你 好吗?\N{\reng}I wanna get to know you better. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.10,1:09:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你很美\N{\reng}I think you're gorgeous.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.99,1:09:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,对了 我觉得你像风一样自由 聪明又灵活\N{\reng}I do. I think you're free as a dang gale and smart as a whip.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.96,1:09:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但我不会做任何事 除非你要我做\N{\reng}But I won't do anything unless you want me to.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.59,1:09:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么样?\N{\reng}How's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.97,1:09:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,这样很好\N{\reng}That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.55,1:09:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\reng}All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.07,1:10:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不知道我对蔡斯到底是什么感觉\N{\reng\i1}I didn't know exactly how I felt about Chase.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.60,1:10:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但我不再孤独了\N{\reng\i1}But I was no longer lonely.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.15,1:10:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这似乎足够了\N{\reng\i1}That seemed enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.72,1:10:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,是为你的书吗?\N{\reng}Is that for your book?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.04,1:10:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\reng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.00,1:10:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,反正 谁知道是否有人会读它\N{\reng}Anyway, who knows if anyone will read it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.07,1:10:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我会\N{\reng}I will.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.22,1:10:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}沼泽是我们的秘密\N{\reng\i1}The marsh was our secret.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.35,1:10:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我关于你的朋友\N{\reng}Tell me about your friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.12,1:10:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 我真的没有任何朋友\N{\reng}Oh, I don't really have any friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.22,1:10:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你和他们在一起的时候似乎总是很开心\N{\reng}You always seem to be having a good time when you're with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.07,1:10:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你在偷窥我?\N{\reng}You spying on me?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.50,1:10:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这很有趣 我爸爸曾告诉我\N{\reng}It's funny. My dad told me once,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.11,1:10:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他喝了点酒 和我妈妈吵了一架\N{\reng}he'd had something to drink and a fight with my mom.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.37,1:10:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他说如果我的朋友真的了解我 他们就不会是我的朋友\N{\reng}He told me if my friends really knew me, they wouldn't be my friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.90,1:11:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道是否有人真正了解我 这就是我要说的\N{\reng}I don't know if anyone really knows me, is what I'm saying, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.87,1:11:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我想知道是什么让天空变蓝\N{\reng}I wonder what makes the sky blue.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.65,1:11:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,来自阳光的蓝色和紫色波长\N{\reng}Blue and violet wavelengths from sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.27,1:11:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,它们被大气中的气体粒子反弹并散射\N{\reng}They, uh, bounce off the gas particles in the atmosphere and scatter.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.61,1:11:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在是否...\N{\reng}Is it okay if I...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.40,1:11:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,可以吻你?\N{\reng}kiss you now?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.32,1:11:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我们来看看蔡斯·安德鲁斯死亡当晚\N{\reng}Let's turn to the red wool fibers found
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.00,1:11:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,在他牛仔外套上发现的\N{\reng}on Chase Andrews' denim jacket
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.92,1:11:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,红色羊毛纤维\N{\reng}the night he died.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.72,1:11:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你把这些样品与这个红色滑雪帽进行了比对吗?\N{\reng}Did you compare those samples to this red ski cap?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.37,1:11:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,证据C\N{\reng}Exhibit C.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.47,1:11:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 帽子和外套的纤维完全吻合\N{\reng}Yes. The fibers from the cap and the jacket matched exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.52,1:11:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,帽子是在哪里找到的呢?\N{\reng}And where was that cap found?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.42,1:12:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,是在克拉克小姐的住所发现的\N{\reng}It was found in Miss Clark's residence.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.65,1:12:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,医生 关于这些红色纤维 有什么办法\N{\reng}Now, about these red fibers, is there any way, doctor,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.45,1:12:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,确定这些纤维在外套上存在了多长时间吗?\N{\reng}to determine how long the fibers had been on the jacket?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.30,1:12:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我们可以知道它来自哪里 而不是何时来\N{\reng}No. We can tell where they came from, not when.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.00,1:12:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有人经常戴这顶帽子\N{\reng}And if someone wore this hat often,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.16,1:12:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,是否有可能纤维会落在他们的头发和衣服上?\N{\reng}is it possible the fibers would be in their hair and on their clothes?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.97,1:12:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 我想有这可能\N{\reng}Yes. I would suppose they could.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.37,1:12:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那你是否同意 在被告克拉克小姐\N{\reng}So would you agree that at any time during the years
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.02,1:12:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,认识蔡斯·安德鲁斯这些年中的任何时候\N{\reng}that the defendant, Miss Clark, knew Chase Andrews,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.80,1:12:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,帽子上的纤维都有可能落到蔡斯的外套上?\N{\reng}the fibers of the hat could have been transferred onto Chase's jacket?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.52,1:12:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,据我所看到的 有可能\N{\reng}From what I've seen, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.10,1:12:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 在他们认识后的任何时候  - 是的\N{\reng}- At any time they met.  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.00,1:12:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“亲爱的克拉克小姐 我们被你的手稿迷住了”\N{\reng}"Dear Miss Clark, we were fascinated by your manuscript."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.75,1:13:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,如果如你所说 你的材料已经很完整了\N{\reng}If, as you say, your materials are already complete,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.50,1:13:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“我们希望在短时间内编辑和出版”\N{\reng}"we hope to edit and publish in record time."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.42,1:13:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 你现在看到的是西部汽车公司的新经理\N{\reng}Hey. You're looking at the new manager of Western Auto.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.93,1:13:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 蔡斯 这是...\N{\reng}Oh, Chase, that's...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.15,1:13:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是个好消息  - 来 我们庆祝一下\N{\reng}- That's great news.  - Come on. Let's celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.45,1:13:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他们会为这些图纸付钱给你?\N{\reng}So they're gonna, uh, pay you for those drawings?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.27,1:13:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\reng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.62,1:13:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,噢\N{\reng}Ooh!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.25,1:13:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我想 只是不要太过自满\N{\reng}Just don't get too full of yourself, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.55,1:13:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会\N{\reng}I wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.63,1:13:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道人们对你很失望\N{\reng}I know people have disappointed you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.30,1:13:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,很抱歉我这么说\N{\reng}And I'm sorry for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.25,1:14:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,被自己的家人抛弃 我是说...\N{\reng}Getting left by your own family. I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.64,1:14:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,天哪 我的家人是个麻烦 让我无法忍受\N{\reng}God, my family's a pain in the ass, but I don't think I could take that.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.80,1:14:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但我想让你知道 我会照顾你\N{\reng}But I want you to know that I'm gonna take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.15,1:14:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我升职了\N{\reng}Now I've been promoted,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.37,1:14:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们结婚后 我可以给你买栋好房子\N{\reng}I can get you a nice house when we're married.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.75,1:14:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- “结婚”?  - 是的\N{\reng}- "Married"?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.70,1:14:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,一栋海滩上的漂亮两层楼 有个环绕阳台\N{\reng}A nice two-story on the beach with a wraparound veranda.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.07,1:14:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\reng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.70,1:14:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,那你父母呢?\N{\reng}What about your parents?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.57,1:14:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你跟他们说过我吗?\N{\reng}Have you told them about me?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.20,1:14:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,关于我父母 你要明白的是\N{\reng}What you gotta understand about my folks
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.45,1:14:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我说你是我的选择 那就是了\N{\reng}is that if I say you're my choice, that'd be that.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.00,1:14:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们了解你后 他们会喜欢你的\N{\reng}They'll fall in love with you when they get to know ya.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.77,1:14:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,过来\N{\reng}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.20,1:14:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 对了 我过几天要开车去阿什维尔\N{\reng}Oh, by the way, I have to drive over to Asheville in a few days
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.86,1:14:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,为我父亲的商店订货\N{\reng}to buy goods for my dad's store.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.10,1:14:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我在想你也可以去\N{\reng}I was thinking you could come.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.60,1:15:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 庆祝你的书和一切  - 噢...\N{\reng}- Celebrate your book and all.  - Oh...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.90,1:15:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那会有很多人  - 这不要紧\N{\reng}- There'd be lots of people.  - It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.05,1:15:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你会跟我一起 我应付一切\N{\reng}You'd be with me. I know everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.52,1:15:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,见鬼 如果你不愿意 你不用和任何人说话\N{\reng}Hell, you don't have to talk to one soul if you don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.22,1:15:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托 如果我们要结婚 你需要到外面的世界看看\N{\reng}Come on. If we're gonna get married, you need to get out in the world a bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.63,1:15:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,展开你那长长的翅膀\N{\reng}Spread those long wings of yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.10,1:15:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧 会很有趣的\N{\reng}Come on. It'll be fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.90,1:15:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个两天的工作 我们会留下过夜\N{\reng}It's a two-day job, so we'll stay the night.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.80,1:15:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,很神奇 是吧?\N{\reng}Incredible, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.00,1:16:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 这是个冒险 来吧\N{\reng}Hey. It's an adventure. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.30,1:17:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你做得越多 以后你就会感觉更好\N{\reng}It'll feel better for you later, the more you do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.40,1:17:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,噢\N{\reng}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.45,1:17:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我永远不愿失去你\N{\reng}Hey, I never wanna lose you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.20,1:17:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是吗?  - 是的\N{\reng}- Yeah?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.37,1:17:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我想了很久\N{\reng}I think about it a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.35,1:17:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上偷偷溜出来看你\N{\reng}Sneaking out at night to come see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.62,1:17:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我的沼泽女孩\N{\reng}My Marsh Girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.60,1:18:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没人知道\N{\reng\i1}Nobody knows
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.64,1:18:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没人看到\N{\reng\i1}Nobody sees
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.52,1:18:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}除了我 没有人知道\N{\reng\i1}Nobody knows but me
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.50,1:18:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 你不需要向任何人证明自己 你明白吗?\N{\reng}Hey, you don't have to prove yourself to anyone. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.77,1:18:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你有我 我也爱你\N{\reng}You have me, and I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.27,1:18:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我给你做了点东西\N{\reng}I made you something.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.20,1:18:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,噢\N{\reng}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.42,1:18:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,那是个单贝壳\N{\reng}It was a single shell,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.40,1:18:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,穿在一根生皮绳上 打了一个很紧的结 但它不见了\N{\reng}hung on a piece of rawhide, tied in a tight knot, and it was missing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.95,1:18:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,因此明确一点 你是说蔡斯每天佩戴的\N{\reng}So to be clear, what you're saying is that the shell necklace
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.57,1:18:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,贝壳项链在他被发现当天\N{\reng}that Chase wore every day was missing from these items
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.70,1:19:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,执法部门从他的身上找到的物品中丢失了\N{\reng}that law enforcement recovered from his body the day that he was found.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.20,1:19:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这样说对吗?\N{\reng}Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.42,1:19:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我想这很重要  - 是的\N{\reng}- I think it's important.  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.45,1:19:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那天晚上他和我们一起吃饭时还戴着那条项链\N{\reng}He had that necklace on when he had dinner with us that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.07,1:19:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,而它从他身上消失了\N{\reng}And it was gone from his body.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.20,1:19:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我要说的是他从来没把它取下过\N{\reng}And what I'm saying is he never took it off.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.92,1:19:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不管是谁杀了他 都拿走了它\N{\reng}Whoever killed him took it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.07,1:19:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,反对 法官大人 这是个猜测\N{\reng}Objection, Your Honor. It's speculation.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.15,1:19:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,反对有效\N{\reng}Sustained.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.70,1:19:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,陪审团的女士们 先生们\N{\reng}Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.32,1:19:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你们不用考虑安德鲁斯夫人最后一句话\N{\reng}you will disregard that last remark by Mrs. Andrews.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.14,1:19:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,安德鲁斯夫人 蔡斯在哪里得到这条项链?\N{\reng}Mrs. Andrews, where did Chase get this necklace?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.68,1:19:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,是沼泽女孩克拉克小姐给的\N{\reng}It's from that Marsh Girl. Miss Clark.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.06,1:19:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我甚至不知道她的名字 也不知道她是否有名字\N{\reng}I didn't even know her name or if she even had one.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.35,1:19:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我不明白为什么蔡斯...\N{\reng}I can't see why Chase...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.10,1:19:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,但我想说的是\N{\reng}But what I'm saying is,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.35,1:19:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,她是唯一一个有动机拿走这个东西的人\N{\reng}she's the only one who'd have any interest in taking the thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.52,1:19:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,安德鲁斯夫人...\N{\reng}Mrs. Andrews...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.10,1:19:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,蔡斯和克拉克小姐有恋爱关系吗?\N{\reng}were Chase and Miss Clark romantically involved?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.20,1:20:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,可以这么认为 我看到他在晚上偷偷溜出去\N{\reng}You could say. I saw him sneaking out at night.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.71,1:20:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,当我最后问他要去哪里时 他告诉了我真相\N{\reng}When I finally asked him where he was going, he told me the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.22,1:20:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我想 人们会怎么说?\N{\reng}I thought: What would people say?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.34,1:20:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我太傻了 竟然担心这个问题...\N{\reng}I was a silly woman to be worried about that next to...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.70,1:20:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,但他告诉我 他和她分手了\N{\reng}But he told me he broke it off with her.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.40,1:20:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,她知道她不能再拥有他 所以她杀了他\N{\reng}She knew she couldn't have him anymore, so she killed him
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.95,1:20:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- 并拿回了她那条丑陋的项链  - 反对 法官大人\N{\reng}- and took back her ugly necklace!  - Objection, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.95,1:20:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,反对有效\N{\reng}Sustained.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.85,1:20:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我问完了 法官大人\N{\reng}No further questions, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.25,1:20:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,安德鲁斯夫人 对你的不幸表示最深切的同情\N{\reng}Um, Mrs. Andrews, you have my deepest sympathy for your loss.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.92,1:20:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,恕我直言\N{\reng}With all due respect,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.17,1:20:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道克拉克小姐的房子被彻底搜查过了\N{\reng}you are aware that Miss Clark's house was thoroughly searched.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.82,1:20:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,但警察在那里没有发现项链\N{\reng}And that the police did not find the necklace there.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.82,1:20:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他们发现了吗?  - 没有\N{\reng}- Did they?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.16,1:21:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\reng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.45,1:21:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我抓住了  - 嘿\N{\reng}- I got it.  - Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.40,1:21:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- 差点撞倒你  - 差点把我撞翻\N{\reng}- Almost got you.  - Almost knocked me out.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.25,1:21:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,就是想炫技\N{\reng}Just trying to show off.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.70,1:21:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,沼泽女孩在床上如何 伙计? 她很狂野吗?\N{\reng}What's that Marsh Girl like in bed, man? Is she an animal?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.43,1:21:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,像山猫一样狂野 花的每一分油钱都值\N{\reng}Wild as a bobcat and worth every bit of the gas money.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.68,1:21:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我她的眼睛会发光\N{\reng}Tell me her eyes glow.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.47,1:21:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 只为我 而且只有在我做的时候  - 嘿 不要这样说她\N{\reng}- Only for me and only when I make them.  - Hey, don't talk about her like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.85,1:21:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- 说什么?  - 我说不要这样说她\N{\reng}- What's that?  - I said don't talk about her like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.22,1:21:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 那个大学生\N{\reng}Oh, the college boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.74,1:21:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他教沼泽女孩认字  - 噢\N{\reng}- He taught the Marsh Girl her ABCs.  - Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.40,1:21:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗯  - 你在浪费她的时间\N{\reng}- Mmm.  - You're a waste of her time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.20,1:21:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,上学去吧 大学生 你想干什么?\N{\reng}Go ahead, college boy. What you gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.72,1:22:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- 来吧 你是硬汉 对吗?  - 来吧 我们做些什么\N{\reng}- Come on, you're tough, right?  - Come on, let's do something.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.87,1:22:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你想打我吗?  - 嘿 你们都冷静点\N{\reng}- You wanna hit me?  - Hey, y'all settle down now.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.25,1:22:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,够了\N{\reng}That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.27,1:22:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,在有人受伤前 都冷静下来\N{\reng}Settle down before someone get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.55,1:22:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,有比这更好的方法\N{\reng}There's better ways than this.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.25,1:22:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 凯雅\N{\reng}Hey, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.07,1:22:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 怎么回事?\N{\reng}Hey, what the hell?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.92,1:22:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 凯雅 等等 拜托\N{\reng}Wait! Kya, wait! Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.08,1:22:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我只是想谈谈\N{\reng}Look, I just wanna talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.22,1:22:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,滚出我的泻湖 你这肮脏的讨厌鬼\N{\reng}Get out of my lagoon, you dirty creep!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.42,1:22:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 求你了 我只是要和你谈谈\N{\reng}Kya, please! I just need to talk to you!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.13,1:22:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我不在乎你想要什么\N{\reng}I don't care what you want!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.47,1:22:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我再也不想见到你 永远\N{\reng}I never wanna see you again. Ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.30,1:22:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 我要和你谈谈蔡斯 好吗?\N{\reng}Kya, I need to talk to you about Chase, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.52,1:22:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谈蔡斯?  - 他配不上你\N{\reng}- About Chase?  - He's not good enough for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.62,1:23:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你才是那个抛弃我的人\N{\reng}You're the one who left me.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.25,1:23:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,你承诺了却没有回来 从未回来过\N{\reng}Who didn't come back when you promised. Who never came back.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.48,1:23:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你甚至没有写信解释 甚至没有说你是死是活\N{\reng}You didn't even write to explain or even to say if you were alive or dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.75,1:23:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你就这样消失了\N{\reng}You just disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.27,1:23:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道 对不起 凯雅 你不知道内情\N{\reng}I know. And I'm so sorry, Kya, you have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.87,1:23:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你不够男人来面对我\N{\reng}You weren't man enough to face me.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.16,1:23:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你说得对 凯雅\N{\reng}You're right, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.67,1:23:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你说的都是事实\N{\reng}Everything you say is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.08,1:23:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,就这么离开你是我做过的最糟糕的事\N{\reng}Leaving you like that was the worst thing I've ever done,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.63,1:23:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,也是我一生中做过最糟糕的事\N{\reng}the worst thing I'll ever do in my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.00,1:23:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道我对你伤害太深 我无法面对你 就像你说的\N{\reng}I knew how badly I'd hurt you, and I couldn't face you, like you said.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.01,1:23:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为你不能离开沼泽 无法生活在其它任何地方\N{\reng}I thought you wouldn't be able to leave the marsh and live in any other world.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.47,1:23:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 我以为我必须在你和其他一切之间做出选择\N{\reng}You know, I thought I had to choose between you and everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.90,1:23:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,但事实是 凯雅 我以为重要的其它一切\N{\reng}But the truth is, Kya, everything else that I thought mattered,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.57,1:23:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,奖学金 补助金 工作 但没有你就都没有意义了\N{\reng}the scholarships, the grants, the jobs, it means nothing without you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.15,1:23:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我大错特错了\N{\reng}I was so wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.41,1:24:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经后悔多年\N{\reng}I've been sorry for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.58,1:24:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,而我的余生都会感到抱歉\N{\reng}And I'll be sorry for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.87,1:24:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你看...\N{\reng}You look...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.10,1:24:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我给你带来一些东西\N{\reng}I brought you something.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.25,1:24:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 我在镇附近的新实验室工作\N{\reng}You know, I'm working at the new lab near town.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.92,1:24:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你会喜欢它 凯雅\N{\reng}You'd love it, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.25,1:24:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以在显微镜下研究这些\N{\reng}I get to study all this under a microscope.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.93,1:25:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我现在来了\N{\reng}So I'm here now.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.47,1:25:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,重归于好\N{\reng}I'm back for good.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.65,1:25:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 我愿做任何事来...\N{\reng}Kya, I would do anything to...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.86,1:25:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以用不同的方式做很多事\N{\reng}I would've done so many things differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.80,1:25:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在想要什么 泰特?\N{\reng}What do you want now, Tate?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.92,1:25:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,有什么办法可以让你原谅我吗 凯雅?\N{\reng}Is there any way that you could possibly forgive me, Kya?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.92,1:25:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,求你了?\N{\reng}Please?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.95,1:25:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道怎么办\N{\reng}I don't know how.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.65,1:26:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 如果你知道其他有理由伤害蔡斯·安德鲁的人\N{\reng}Kya, I trust you would tell me if you knew of anyone else
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.82,1:26:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信你会告诉我\N{\reng}who had reason to harm Chase Andrews.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.12,1:26:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 那好吧\N{\reng}Well, all right, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.51,1:26:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,去休息一下吧\N{\reng}Try and get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.50,1:26:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 嗨\N{\reng}Oh. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.27,1:26:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 你来镇上做什么?\N{\reng}Hey. What you doing in town?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.60,1:26:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我从出版商那里得到些好消息 所以我想我们可以庆祝一下\N{\reng}I had some good news from the publisher, so I thought we could celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.97,1:26:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 本来打算...  - 他在那里\N{\reng}- Was gonna make...  - There he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.92,1:26:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 你认识布莱恩 蒂娜 珀尔\N{\reng}Kya, you know Brian, Tina, Pearl.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.77,1:26:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你们都认识凯雅  - 当然认识 沼泽女孩\N{\reng}- You guys know Kya.  - Sure, yeah, the Marsh Girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.45,1:26:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴见到你 凯雅\N{\reng}Pleased to meet you, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.40,1:26:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我是蔡斯的未婚妻\N{\reng}I'm Chase's fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.50,1:27:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 呃 我们回头见 凯雅\N{\reng}All right. Well, I'll see you around, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.60,1:27:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.88,1:27:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 我可以解释\N{\reng}Hey, Kya. I can explain.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.77,1:27:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你在里面吗?\N{\reng}Are you in there?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.92,1:27:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是想谈谈\N{\reng}Hey, I just wanna talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.35,1:27:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.62,1:28:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你在 该死的\N{\reng}I know you're here, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.86,1:28:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.65,1:29:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我注定要独自生活\N{\reng\i1}I had to do life alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.63,1:29:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但我知道这点\N{\reng\i1}But I knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.38,1:29:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我已经知道很久了\N{\reng\i1}I'd known for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.27,1:29:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}人们不会留下\N{\reng\i1}People don't stay.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.87,1:29:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}“亲爱的克拉克小姐\N{\reng\i1}"Dear Miss Clark,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.60,1:29:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}随信附上你那本精美作品的最终版本\N{\reng\i1}enclosed is the final copy of your beautiful book,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.15,1:29:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以及出版的首签支票\N{\reng\i1}along with the initial check for delivery,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.60,1:29:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我肯定版权费也会随后到来\N{\reng\i1}with royalties to follow, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.92,1:29:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我下个月要参加在格林维尔举行的会议\N{\reng\i1}I'm attending a conference in Greenville next month
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.65,1:29:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并希望你能参加以庆祝这一了不起的成就”\N{\reng\i1}and would love for you to join us and celebrate this great accomplishment."
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.20,1:29:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}“凯瑟琳·丹妮尔·克拉克的完整契约\N{\reng\i1}}"A full deed for Catherine Danielle Clark
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.01,1:30:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}包括310英亩泻湖 沼泽 橡树林和海滩\N{\reng\i1}}for 310 acres of lagoons, marsh, oak forests and beach.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.89,1:30:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}荒地类别 浊水沼泽”\N{\reng\i1}}Wasteland category: murky swamp."
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.82,1:30:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,乔迪?\N{\reng}Jodie?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.60,1:30:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我在阿什维尔一家商店里看到你的书\N{\reng}There I am in Asheville, and I see your book in a shop:
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.62,1:30:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳·丹妮尔·克拉克\N{\reng}Catherine Danielle Clark.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.32,1:30:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我一下子呆住了 同时也非常开心\N{\reng}And my heart just broke and leapt for joy all at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.37,1:30:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道我必须找到你\N{\reng}I knew I had to find you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.75,1:30:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是没想到你还在这里\N{\reng}I just didn't think you'd still be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.56,1:30:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,其他人呢?\N{\reng}What about the others?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.80,1:30:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我对墨菲 曼迪和米茜一无所知\N{\reng}I don't know a thing about Murph, Mandy or Missy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.82,1:30:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我在街上遇到他们都认不出了\N{\reng}I wouldn't know them if I passed them in the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.86,1:30:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,还有 呃...\N{\reng}And, um...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.90,1:30:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈呢?\N{\reng}what about Ma?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.12,1:31:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈死了 凯雅\N{\reng}Ma passed, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.30,1:31:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈有个妹妹 叫罗斯玛丽\N{\reng}Ma had a sister, Rosemary.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.67,1:31:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,她来部队里找到我 告诉我发生了什么\N{\reng}She found me in the Army and told me what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.92,1:31:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈穿着鳄鱼皮鞋出现在罗斯玛丽家门口\N{\reng}Showed up at Rosemary's door in her alligator shoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.22,1:31:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,罗斯玛丽说她有几个月没说话\N{\reng}Rosemary said she didn't talk for months.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.70,1:31:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,然后大约一年后 她想起了自己有孩子\N{\reng}And then about a year later, she remembered she had children.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.82,1:31:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,罗斯玛丽帮她给爸爸写了一封信 问她是否可以来接我们\N{\reng}Rosemary helped her write a letter to Pa, asking if she could come get us.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.69,1:31:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸告诉她 如果她再了我们联系的话\N{\reng}And he told her if she ever so much as contacted us again,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.45,1:31:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,就把我们揍得面目全非\N{\reng}he'd beat us unrecognizable.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.53,1:31:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,对 听起来像爸爸\N{\reng}Yeah, sounds like Pa.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.90,1:31:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,她为律师和所有事都攒了钱\N{\reng}She saved up for lawyers and everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.42,1:31:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但后来她生病了\N{\reng}but then she got sick.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.95,1:31:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,白血病\N{\reng}Leukemia.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.90,1:31:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,她努力了 但...\N{\reng}She tried, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.12,1:31:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,她从未有过机会\N{\reng}She never had a chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.27,1:31:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直在等待...\N{\reng}I've been waiting...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.92,1:31:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,多年来 她一直走在这条小路上\N{\reng}all these years for her to walk down the lane.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.05,1:31:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你的一生都没有家庭\N{\reng}You didn't have a family your whole life,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.18,1:32:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,而我没有办法把它还给你\N{\reng}and there's nothing I can do to give you that back.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.72,1:32:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,但我希望尽可能多的来看你 只要我能上来\N{\reng}But I'd like to come see you as much as I can get up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.57,1:32:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,好 我喜欢这样\N{\reng}Yeah, I'd like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.85,1:32:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs17\pos(192,276)\c&HF6F6F6&\1a&H23&}给羽毛男孩 谢谢你  来自沼泽女孩
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.31,1:32:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,梅布尔肯定很骄傲\N{\reng}Mabel's gonna be so proud.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.30,1:32:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,还有一件事\N{\reng}Just one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.07,1:32:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我保证交给他\N{\reng}I'll be sure he gets it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.15,1:33:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 朱姆平\N{\reng}Thank you, Jumpin'.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.45,1:33:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你们都好吗?\N{\reng}How y'all doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.70,1:33:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,请给我一包最好的 先生\N{\reng}One pack of your finest, please, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.58,1:33:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,再给我一些火柴\N{\reng}And give me some matches.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.17,1:33:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 肯定的  - “肯定的”\N{\reng}- Sure thing.  - "Sure thing."
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.79,1:33:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅·克拉克\N{\reng}Kya Clark.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.10,1:33:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳·丹妮尔·克拉克小姐\N{\reng}Miss Catherine Danielle Clark.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.97,1:33:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你写了本该死的书 过来\N{\reng}You wrote a damn book. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.92,1:33:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 等等 等等 我想和你谈谈\N{\reng}Wait, wait, wait. I wanna talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.82,1:33:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,不要这样 来吧\N{\reng}Don't act like that. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.65,1:33:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,别来烦我\N{\reng}Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.73,1:33:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 该死的  - 沼泽女孩觉得她现在对你太好了\N{\reng}- Damn,  - the Marsh Girl thinks she's too good for you now.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.06,1:33:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,闭嘴\N{\reng}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.15,1:33:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,给你 先生 这是免费的\N{\reng}Here you go, sir. It's on the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.02,1:33:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我想可能会在这里找到你\N{\reng}Thought I might find you here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.83,1:33:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我告诉过你别来烦我\N{\reng}I told you to leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.35,1:33:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我知道 我只是... 听着 我想说很抱歉\N{\reng}No, I know, but I just... Listen, I wanted to say I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.82,1:33:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,真的 我对这样的结果感到难过\N{\reng}Really. I feel bad about how things turned out.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.47,1:33:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“这样的结果”?\N{\reng}"How things turned out"?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.34,1:34:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,什么 你是说我们在一起时\N{\reng}What, you mean how it turned out
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.10,1:34:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你一直都有个未婚妻吗?\N{\reng}you were engaged the whole time we were together?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.80,1:34:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,结果是你对所有人都撒谎了吗?\N{\reng}How it turned out that you lie to everybody?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.10,1:34:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 我不得不做我不想做的事 你知道的\N{\reng}Kya, I have to do things I don't wanna do. You know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.87,1:34:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,对 我必须娶像珀尔这样的人 我只能这么做\N{\reng}No, I have to get married to someone like Pearl. I had to.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.82,1:34:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,但你才是我真正想要的人\N{\reng}But you're the one I really want.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.07,1:34:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道其他的男人都想改变你吗?\N{\reng}You know any other man would have tried to change you?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.10,1:34:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,来修正你?\N{\reng}To fix you?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.75,1:34:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但我从未做过\N{\reng}I never did.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.30,1:34:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,不 拜托 拜托 等等 我需要你 我真的需要你\N{\reng}No, no. Please, please, wait. I need you. I really need you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.58,1:34:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不要让我一个人待在那地方\N{\reng}Don't leave me all alone in that place.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.45,1:34:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道 没有人了解我\N{\reng}You know, nobody else knows me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.25,1:34:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 我为你感到遗憾\N{\reng}You know, I feel sorry for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.25,1:34:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,但我不想和这些事有任何关系\N{\reng}But I want nothing to do with any of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.67,1:35:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,比以往更野了\N{\reng}Wilder than ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.20,1:35:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你也想这样\N{\reng}I know you want this too.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.82,1:35:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 住手  - 我知道你也想要\N{\reng}- Stop!  - I know you want this too.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.46,1:35:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你是我的 凯雅 你属于我 这次我不会再让你走了\N{\reng}You're mine, Kya. You belong to me. I'm not letting you go this time.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.15,1:35:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,离我远点 你这混蛋\N{\reng}Leave me alone, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.69,1:35:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你再来烦我 我就杀了你\N{\reng}You bother me again and I'll kill you!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.55,1:35:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,她喊得很大声 先生\N{\reng}She shouted it real loud, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.75,1:35:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我听到一阵骚动 我走近一看\N{\reng}I heard a commotion, and I come closer,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.92,1:35:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,看看是否有人遇到麻烦 她就在那里\N{\reng}see if anybody was in trouble, and there she was.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.37,1:35:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,那你认识这个女人吗?\N{\reng}And do you recognize the woman?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.82,1:36:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,她今天在法庭上吗?\N{\reng}Is she in the courtroom today?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.50,1:36:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 那里的那个人 被告人\N{\reng}Yes, that one there. The defendant.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.52,1:36:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,大伙称之为沼泽女孩的\N{\reng}The one folks call Marsh Girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.72,1:36:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我终于明白妈妈为什么离开了\N{\reng\i1}I finally understood why Ma had to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.45,1:37:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我从爸爸那里学到一件事\N{\reng\i1}One thing I learned from Pa,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.70,1:37:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些人必须被最后一击\N{\reng\i1}these men have to have the last punch.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.90,1:37:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}被孤立是一回事\N{\reng\i1}Being isolated was one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.85,1:38:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}生活在恐惧中是另一回事\N{\reng\i1}Living in fear, quite another.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.72,1:38:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我永远不会像那样生活\N{\reng\i1}I will never live like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.87,1:38:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一生都在担心下一次打击\N{\reng\i1}A life wondering when the next fist will fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.72,1:38:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,泰特 你不能在这里\N{\reng}Tate, you can't be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.55,1:38:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是想来看看你\N{\reng}I just wanted to check on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.25,1:38:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- 朱姆平说他没有见过你 因为...  - 现在不行\N{\reng}- Jumpin' said he hadn't seen you since...  - Not now.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.32,1:38:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 你的脸怎么了?\N{\reng}Kya, what happened to your face?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.70,1:38:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,是蔡斯吗? 告诉我 凯雅 是他干的吗?\N{\reng}Was it Chase? Tell me, Kya. Did he do this?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.75,1:38:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你不要插手这件事\N{\reng}I need you to stay out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.22,1:38:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这个狗东西\N{\reng}That son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.09,1:38:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这狗娘养的  - 泰特 我要你走\N{\reng}- That son of a bitch.  - Tate, I need you to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.40,1:38:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.76,1:39:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,知道吗 我本打算下周去格林维尔\N{\reng}You know, I was gonna go to Greenville next week.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.10,1:39:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,总算能见到我的出版商了\N{\reng}Finally meet my publishers.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.90,1:39:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,谈谈下一本书\N{\reng}Talk about the next book.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.20,1:39:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得自己足够勇敢\N{\reng}I was feeling brave enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.00,1:39:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你仍然可以去\N{\reng}Well, you can still go.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.95,1:39:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,就这样子去吗?\N{\reng}Looking like this?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.70,1:39:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,不要让他毁了你的事\N{\reng}Don't let him ruin this for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.35,1:39:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,去格林维尔\N{\reng}Go to Greenville.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.37,1:39:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,好吗? 这里有班车\N{\reng}Okay? There's a bus.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.02,1:39:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,很简单 朱姆平有班车时间表\N{\reng}It's easy. Jumpin's got the schedule.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.72,1:39:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,让他们给你安排一个好旅馆\N{\reng}Let them put you up in a nice hotel,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.17,1:39:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,吃一些你不用做的餐厅热食物\N{\reng}eat some hot restaurant food you didn't have to make.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.72,1:39:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,如果可以就待一周\N{\reng}Stay a week, if you can.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.62,1:39:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你回来后我就来看你 好吗?\N{\reng}And I'll come see you when you're back. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.32,1:39:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我出版商的进展如何\N{\reng}Hear how it all went with the publishers.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.27,1:39:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\reng}All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.67,1:39:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿 你冷吗?\N{\reng}Hey, you cold?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.45,1:39:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我很好 我不需要你来关心我\N{\reng}I'm fine. I don't need you to take care of me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.55,1:39:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道 拿着我的帽子\N{\reng}I know, but just take my hat.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.90,1:39:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我说了不需要你帮助  - 拿着吧\N{\reng}- I said I don't need your help.  - Just take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.87,1:40:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你想告诉我你的眼睛怎么了吗?\N{\reng}You wanna tell me what happened to your eye?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.90,1:40:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要公交车的时间表\N{\reng}I need to write down the bus schedule.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.22,1:40:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你有副本 对吧?\N{\reng}You have a copy, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.97,1:40:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,是那个蔡斯 不是吗?\N{\reng}It was that Chase, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.20,1:40:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 看着我\N{\reng}Kya, look at me.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.62,1:40:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,现在告诉我 他做了什么\N{\reng}Now you tell me what he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.92,1:40:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我不能说\N{\reng}I can't say it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.75,1:40:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,已经结束了\N{\reng}It's over now.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.65,1:41:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我只想这事从我生活中消失\N{\reng}I just want it out of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.52,1:41:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道他不会再来找你呢?\N{\reng}And how you know he ain't coming after you again?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.07,1:41:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你在外面孤零零一个人  - 朱姆平 拜托\N{\reng}- You're all by your lonesome out there.  - Jumpin', please.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.05,1:41:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能告诉任何人\N{\reng}You can't tell anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.44,1:41:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道这会怎么样\N{\reng}You know how it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.87,1:41:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会把我带到警长办公室 让我向一帮人描述情况\N{\reng}They'd drag me into the sheriff's office and make me describe it to a bunch of men.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.25,1:41:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,然后在报纸上攻击我 指责我卖淫\N{\reng}And then write me up in the papers, accusing me of whoring.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.77,1:41:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,或者想从他的父母那里得到钱\N{\reng}Or trying to get money out of his parents.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.70,1:41:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,好吗? 他们不会做任何事\N{\reng}Okay? They'd do nothing about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.45,1:41:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你是对的 凯雅\N{\reng}You're right, Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.10,1:41:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会做任何事让这件事变得更糟\N{\reng}And I ain't gonna do anything to make this thing worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.75,1:41:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,但你要告诉我你什么时候去 什么时候回来\N{\reng}But you let me know when you're coming and going.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.10,1:41:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,听到了吗?\N{\reng}You hear?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.02,1:41:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我得知道你是否离开了镇子\N{\reng}I gotta know if you're out of town.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.30,1:41:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,因为如果我有段时间没见到你...\N{\reng}'Cause if I don't see you for a while...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.97,1:41:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 朱姆平\N{\reng}Thank you, Jumpin'.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.32,1:41:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我过几天就走\N{\reng}I'm leaving in a few days.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.62,1:42:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我一回来就来看你\N{\reng}I'll come see you as soon as I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.57,1:42:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 这样很好\N{\reng}Okay, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.62,1:42:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这样很好\N{\reng}That's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.54,1:42:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,普莱斯小姐 你能告诉我们你在10月29日早上看到了什么吗?\N{\reng}Miss Price, would you tell us what you saw on the morning of October 29?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.17,1:42:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我看到沼泽女孩...\N{\reng}I saw the Marsh Girl...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.96,1:42:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,克拉克小姐 请原谅\N{\reng}Miss Clark, that is. Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.80,1:42:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- 上了9点的车  - 你的记忆力挺好\N{\reng}- Get on the 9:00 bus.  - You've got quite a good memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.05,1:42:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都在谈这件事\N{\reng}We all talked about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.22,1:42:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们从未见过她如此的打扮\N{\reng\i1}We'd never seen her all cleaned up like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.55,1:42:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}头发梳起来 化了妆\N{\reng\i1}Hair combed, makeup.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.67,1:42:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}明确的说 在10月29日上午\N{\reng\i1}Just to be clear, on the morning of October 29,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.22,1:42:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你和其他几个人看到克拉克小姐上了上午9点的班车\N{\reng\i1}you and several others saw Miss Clark board the 9 a.m. bus
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.07,1:42:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}离开了巴克利湾\N{\reng\i1}and leave Barkley Cove.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.15,1:42:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是的 没错  - 谢谢你 普莱斯小姐\N{\reng}- Yes, that's right.  - Thank you, Miss Price.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.22,1:42:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,没有其他问题了 法官大人\N{\reng}No further questions, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.05,1:42:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,普莱斯小姐 小猪佩奇在凌晨1点半开门吗?\N{\reng}Miss Price, is the Piggly Wiggly open at 1:30 in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.78,1:42:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,没有 先生\N{\reng}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.12,1:42:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我问的原因是\N{\reng}Well, the reason I ask is,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.30,1:42:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你不可能看到谁从格林维尔的夜班车上下来了\N{\reng}you couldn't have seen who got off the night bus from Greenville,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.05,1:43:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你也不可能看到谁上了凌晨2点半的班车\N{\reng}nor could you have seen who got on the 2:30 a.m. bus
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.90,1:43:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,从巴克利湾回到格林维尔 你能吗?\N{\reng}from Barkley Cove back to Greenville, could you?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.45,1:43:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 不 当然不能\N{\reng}Well, no. Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.17,1:43:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,因此在你看到克拉克小姐登上开往格林维尔的早班车后...\N{\reng}So after you saw Miss Clark board that morning bus to Greenville...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.72,1:43:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,她可以在当天晚上回到巴克利湾\N{\reng}she could have returned to Barkley Cove that night
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.65,1:43:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,并回格林维尔吃早餐 这些都不会引起你的注意\N{\reng}and been back in Greenville for breakfast, all without you taking notice.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.62,1:43:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫罗伯特·福斯特\N{\reng}My name is Robert Foster.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.07,1:43:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我是波士顿哈里森·莫里斯出版公司的\N{\reng}I'm a senior editor at Harrison Morris Publishing Company
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.20,1:43:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,一名高级编辑\N{\reng}in Boston, Massachusetts.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.42,1:43:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,福斯特先生 你在10月29日晚上7点和克拉克小姐\N{\reng}Mr. Foster, you sat down for dinner with Miss Clark at 7 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.82,1:43:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,坐在一起进餐\N{\reng}on the night of October 29.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.97,1:43:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对吗?  - 对\N{\reng}- Correct?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.20,1:43:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你对她的第一印象是什么?\N{\reng}What was your first impression of her?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.75,1:43:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我的第一印象是 她很害羞 非常温柔 非常聪明\N{\reng}My first impression was, uh, that she was very shy, very gentle, very smart.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.34,1:43:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道她是个隐居者\N{\reng}I knew that she was something of a recluse,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.22,1:43:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,但我也知道 她是个有天赋的自然学家\N{\reng}but I also knew that she was a gifted naturalist.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.27,1:43:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那次晚宴持续了多久?  - 至少几个小时\N{\reng}- How long did that dinner go on?  - At least a few hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.22,1:43:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,一些雌性昆虫确实会吃掉它们的配偶\N{\reng}Some female insects do eat their mates.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.10,1:43:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上 萤火虫有两种不同的光信号\N{\reng}Fireflies, in fact, have two different light signals.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.31,1:43:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,一种用于交配\N{\reng}One for mating,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.52,1:44:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,还有一种是为吸引雄性 以便让它成为她的下一餐\N{\reng}and one to attract a male in order to make him her next meal.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.61,1:44:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 所以她吃了他?  - 好恐怖\N{\reng}- So she eats him?  - How gruesome.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.35,1:44:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- 亲爱的  - 我必须少跟昆虫打交道\N{\reng}- Oh, dear.  - I must spend less time with insects.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.19,1:44:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这很不道德  - 确实不道德\N{\reng}- It's quite amoral.  - Amoral, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.67,1:44:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道大自然是否有黑暗的一面\N{\reng}I don't know if there is a dark side to nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.70,1:44:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,或仅是一种奇妙的生存方式\N{\reng}Just inventive ways to endure.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.79,1:44:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,不惜代价\N{\reng}Against all odds.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.05,1:44:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你在次日早上 也就是10月30日与克拉克小姐见面时\N{\reng}And when you met with Miss Clark the following morning, October 30th,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.63,1:44:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,她的外表或举止是否有任何不寻常之处?\N{\reng}was there anything unusual about her appearance or her demeanor?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.07,1:44:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,完全没有\N{\reng}Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.47,1:44:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我问完了 法官大人\N{\reng}No further questions, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.22,1:44:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,福斯特先生 克拉克小姐是否与你\N{\reng}Mr. Foster, did Miss Clark stay
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.77,1:44:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,和你的同事住在同一家酒店?\N{\reng}at the same hotel as you and your colleagues?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.62,1:44:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,没有 她更喜欢小点的酒店\N{\reng}No. She preferred a smaller hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.30,1:44:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,那个 叫什么山\N{\reng}The, uh, Mountain something.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.81,1:44:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,请你看看这张格林维尔的地图 好吗?\N{\reng}Could you look at this map of Greenville for me, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.17,1:44:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你会看到皮德蒙特酒店 你和你的同事就住在那里\N{\reng}I think you'll see The Piedmont, where you and your colleagues stayed,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.85,1:44:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,然后是三山酒店 克拉克小姐住在那里\N{\reng}and then The Three Mountains Hotel, where Miss Clark stayed.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.97,1:44:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你能告诉我哪一家离汽车站最近吗?\N{\reng}Could you tell me which one is closest to the bus station?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.15,1:44:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,三山酒店比较近\N{\reng}The Three Mountains Hotel is closer.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.57,1:45:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上 三山是距离格林维尔车站\N{\reng}In fact, The Three Mountains is the closest hotel
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.42,1:45:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,最近的酒店 是这样吗?\N{\reng}to the Greenville bus station. Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.82,1:45:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,看起来对的\N{\reng}Looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.87,1:45:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我问完了\N{\reng}No further questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.51,1:45:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我不认为一个好律师会让他们的客户出庭作证\N{\reng}I don't think a good lawyer ever puts their client on the stand,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.12,1:45:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,但这可能有助于你\N{\reng}but this might help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.39,1:45:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,为了让陪审团能直接听到你的心声\N{\reng}For the jury to be able to hear from you, directly.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.00,1:45:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,为了让他们能看到你...\N{\reng}For them to be able to see you...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.40,1:45:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,是一个真正的善良和体贴的人\N{\reng}as the kind and thoughtful person you truly are.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.10,1:45:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,他们永远不会这样看我\N{\reng}They're never gonna see me like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.87,1:45:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,听着 我知道你有很多理由来恨这些人...\N{\reng}Listen. I know you have a world of reasons to hate these people...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.30,1:45:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我从来没有恨过他们\N{\reng}No, I never hated them.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.22,1:45:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,是他们憎恨我\N{\reng}They hated me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.65,1:45:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他们嘲笑我 他们抛弃了我\N{\reng}They laughed at me. They left me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.37,1:45:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他们骚扰我 他们攻击我\N{\reng}They harassed me. They attacked me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.02,1:45:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你... 你想让我乞求活命吗?\N{\reng}You... You want me to beg for my life?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.88,1:45:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会乞求\N{\reng}I don't have it in me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.72,1:45:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会\N{\reng}I won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.60,1:45:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会献祭自己\N{\reng}I will not offer myself up.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.25,1:45:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,他们可以做出自己的决定\N{\reng}They can make their decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.25,1:46:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们不能决定我是谁\N{\reng}But they're not deciding anything about me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.87,1:46:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是他们\N{\reng}It's them.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.75,1:46:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,他们在审判自己\N{\reng}They're judging themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.02,1:46:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,那好吧\N{\reng}All right, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.55,1:46:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,米尔顿先生 你一直对我很好\N{\reng}Mr. Milton, you have always been kind to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.22,1:46:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,即使在小时候\N{\reng}Even as a child.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.30,1:46:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我从未忘记\N{\reng}I never forgot.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.67,1:46:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他的生命被那个无法接受\N{\reng\i1}His life was cut short by the jilted lover
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.44,1:46:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他回归家庭并被抛弃的情人扼杀了\N{\reng\i1}who could not accept that he had returned to the fold.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.19,1:46:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一名证人看到克拉克小姐和蔡斯在沼泽地里\N{\reng\i1}A witness saw Miss Clark and Chase in the marsh.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.77,1:46:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}听到她说“我要杀了你”这句话\N{\reng\i1}Heard her say the words "I'll kill you."
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.92,1:46:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}更重要的是\N{\reng\i1}And what's more,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.67,1:47:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是有当晚的物证将他们联系起来\N{\reng\i1}is there's physical evidence from that night connecting them.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.55,1:47:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她的红色羊绒帽上的纤维\N{\reng\i1}Fibers from her red wool cap
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.00,1:47:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}留在他的牛仔外套上\N{\reng\i1}left on his denim jacket.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.10,1:47:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}爸爸 我要去处理一下\N{\reng\i1}Dad, I'm going over to deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.54,1:47:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有谁会有动机拿走那条贝壳项链?\N{\reng\i1}Who else would have motive to take that shell necklace?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.72,1:47:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你们能够并且必须\N{\reng}You can, and you must,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.35,1:47:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,裁定被告犯有一级谋杀罪\N{\reng}find that the defendant is guilty of first-degree murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.48,1:47:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,米尔顿先生\N{\reng}Mr. Milton.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.42,1:47:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我一生都生活在巴克利湾\N{\reng}I have lived in Barkley Cove my whole life.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.80,1:47:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,和你们一样 我也听过那些关于\N{\reng}And like you, I heard the tall tales
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.92,1:47:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,沼泽女孩的传说\N{\reng}told about the Marsh Girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.30,1:48:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,她是半狼人\N{\reng}That she was part wolf.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.90,1:48:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,是猿类和人类之间缺失的一环\N{\reng}A missing link between ape and man.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.85,1:48:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,她的眼睛会在黑暗中发光\N{\reng}That her eyes glowed in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.10,1:48:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 她在这里\N{\reng}Well, here she is.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.65,1:48:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,事实是 她是个被遗弃的孩子\N{\reng}The reality is that she was an abandoned child.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.66,1:48:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,一个独自在沼泽地里生存的小姑娘\N{\reng}A little girl surviving out there in the marsh on her own,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.57,1:48:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,被人谩骂和排斥\N{\reng}reviled and shunned.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.92,1:48:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯·麦迪逊先生和他的妻子梅布尔\N{\reng}Mr. James Madison and his wife, Mabel,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.34,1:48:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,他们今天就坐在法庭上\N{\reng}they are sitting here in the courtroom today.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.80,1:48:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他们是这个镇上唯一对她表示关心的人\N{\reng}They're about the only people in this town who showed her any care.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.85,1:48:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我们其他人...\N{\reng}The rest of us...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.52,1:48:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 我很惭愧的说\N{\reng}Well, I'm ashamed to say
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.56,1:48:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我们给她贴上标签并排斥她是因为我们觉得她与众不同\N{\reng}that we labeled her and rejected her because we thought she was different.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.15,1:48:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,而现在...\N{\reng}And now...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.07,1:48:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,判定这个害羞和被排斥的年轻女子的工作\N{\reng}the job of judging this shy and rejected young woman
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.97,1:49:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,已经落在你们的肩上\N{\reng}has fallen on your shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.65,1:49:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,但你们必须根据在这个法庭上提出的事实进行判定\N{\reng}But you must base your judgment on the facts presented in this courtroom,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.08,1:49:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是在过去25年的传言和感觉上\N{\reng}and not on the rumors and feelings from the past 25 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.47,1:49:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,克拉克小姐有可靠的不在场证明\N{\reng}Miss Clark has a solid alibi.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.32,1:49:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,蔡斯·安德鲁死的那天晚上 她在格林维尔\N{\reng}She was in Greenville the night Chase Andrews died.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.72,1:49:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,那么究竟是什么事实对她不利呢?\N{\reng}And what facts, exactly, stand against her?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.32,1:49:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,控方没有证明这一事件是一起谋杀案\N{\reng}The State has not proven that this incident was indeed a murder,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.55,1:49:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,而不仅仅是一起悲惨事故\N{\reng}and not just some tragic accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.52,1:49:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,控方想让你们相信 在晚上11点半\N{\reng}The State wants you to believe that at 11:30 at night,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.37,1:49:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,没有一个目击证人的情况下\N{\reng}without a single witness seeing her,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.90,1:49:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,她赶上了从格林维尔到巴克利湾的最后一班车\N{\reng}she caught the last bus from Greenville to Barkley Cove,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.37,1:49:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,而且乔装打扮坐上那辆车\N{\reng}and rode that bus disguised,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.12,1:49:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,因为当晚的公交车司机都无法认出\N{\reng}since neither of the bus drivers that night could identify her
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.50,1:49:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,她是其中一名乘客 并一直回到巴克利湾\N{\reng}as a passenger, all the way back to Barkley Cove.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.75,1:49:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,然后 在不到一小时内...\N{\reng}And then, in less than an hour...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.17,1:50:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,她在半夜跟踪蔡斯·安德鲁斯\N{\reng}she tracks down Chase Andrews in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.27,1:50:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,把他引诱到塔上 谋杀了他\N{\reng}lures him to the tower, murders him,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.72,1:50:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,并抹去了所有物证\N{\reng}wipes away all physical evidence,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.12,1:50:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,又莫名其妙搭上凌晨2点半的班车回到格林维尔\N{\reng}and somehow catches the 2:30 a.m. bus back to Greenville.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.02,1:50:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,同样 也没有一个目击证人\N{\reng}Again, without a single witness seeing her.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.45,1:50:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,做完这一切后\N{\reng}And after doing all that,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.65,1:50:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,第二天早上 她和她的出版商见面 没有任何异常\N{\reng}she meets with her publishers the next morning, unruffled.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.35,1:50:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,但这些并不是事实\N{\reng}Now, these are not facts.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.95,1:50:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,这些只是我们一直在\N{\reng}These are just more of the rumors
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.90,1:50:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,传播的关于克拉克小姐一生的谣言和荒缪故事\N{\reng}and tall tales that we have been spreading about Miss Clark her entire life.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.15,1:50:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信你们会根据事实做出判断\N{\reng}I believe you will come to a judgment based on the facts,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.17,1:50:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是你们多年来听到的流言蜚语\N{\reng}and not the gossip that you have heard for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.57,1:50:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,终于到了\N{\reng}It's time, at last,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.97,1:50:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我们所有人都能公平对待沼泽女孩的时候了\N{\reng}for all of us to be fair to the Marsh Girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.30,1:50:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,也许你们应该回家 在家里等待\N{\reng}Maybe you should go home and do your waiting there.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.65,1:50:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,已经六个小时了 你觉得他们会花多长时间?\N{\reng}Six hours already. How long do you think they'll take?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.37,1:51:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 希望他们能多花些时间\N{\reng}Well, let's hope they take a good long while.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.02,1:51:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有些陪审员有疑虑 我们就有机会了\N{\reng}If a few jurors have doubts, we got a chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.72,1:51:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,福尔曼先生 陪审团已经达成了裁决吗?\N{\reng}Mr. Foreman, is it correct that the jury has reached a verdict?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.20,1:51:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,达成了 法官大人\N{\reng}We have, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.67,1:51:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,请被告人起立 宣读判决书\N{\reng}The defendant will please rise for the reading of the verdict.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.61,1:51:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,站起来\N{\reng}Stand up.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.65,1:52:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“我们陪审团认为 被告凯瑟琳·丹尼尔·克拉克...\N{\reng}"We, the jury, find the defendant, Catherine Danielle Clark...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:04.25,1:52:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,对蔡斯·安德鲁先生的一级谋杀罪名不成立”\N{\reng}not guilty of first-degree murder of Mr. Chase Andrews."
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.95,1:52:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,克拉克小姐 你可以走了\N{\reng}Miss Clark, you are free to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.67,1:52:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我代表州法院对你被拘押的时间表示歉意\N{\reng}And I apologize, on behalf of the State, for the time that you have served.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.52,1:52:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,本庭驳回诉讼\N{\reng}This court is dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.37,1:52:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\reng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.85,1:52:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,过来\N{\reng}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.17,1:52:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你没事 你没事了\N{\reng}You're okay. You're all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.38,1:52:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,忘了这些不愉快的事吧 我们期待你的下一本书\N{\reng}You just forget about this nonsense. We're looking forward to the next book.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.05,1:53:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你能带我回家吗?\N{\reng}Can you take me home?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.61,1:53:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs17\pos(192,30)\c&HF6F6F6&\1a&H1F&}为你的海鸥  - 泰特
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.74,1:53:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}现在我终于可以承认\N{\reng\i1}Now I can finally admit.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.85,1:53:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在与世隔绝的几个月里 我渴望回到沼泽地\N{\reng\i1}All the months in isolation, yearning to be back in the marsh,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:00.05,1:54:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为知道还有多少东西需要探索\N{\reng\i1}it was knowing how much was left to explore,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.47,1:54:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还有多少生命需要在野外发现\N{\reng\i1}how much life to uncover in the wild,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.20,1:54:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这让我坚持了下来\N{\reng\i1}that kept me going.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:09.90,1:54:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以及希望\N{\reng\i1}And the hope,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.72,1:54:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一直希望...\N{\reng\i1}always that hope...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.65,1:54:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有一天我可以和我...\N{\reng\i1}that one day I could share it...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:19.07,1:54:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}唯一真正爱过的人一起分享它\N{\reng\i1}with the only person I had ever truly loved.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.90,1:54:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.07,1:54:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.94,1:55:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\reng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.75,1:55:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道我喜欢你 对吗?\N{\reng}You know I love you, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.72,1:56:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了?\N{\reng}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:21.43,1:56:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你愿意...? 抱歉 很抱歉\N{\reng}Will you, uh...? Sorry. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.12,1:56:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你愿意嫁给我吗?\N{\reng}Will you marry me?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:29.95,1:56:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 你想这样吗?\N{\reng}I mean, do you want to?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.86,1:56:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不是已经这样了吗?\N{\reng}Well, aren't we already?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.03,1:56:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,像天鹅那样?\N{\reng}Like geese?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.16,1:56:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我可以接受这说法\N{\reng}I can live with that, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:46.50,1:56:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,过来\N{\reng}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.00,1:57:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,噢 我们到了\N{\reng}Oh, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.80,1:57:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\reng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:02.72,1:57:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 你 嗨 你们好\N{\reng}Hey, you. Hi, there.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:11.20,1:57:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,过来 小宝贝\N{\reng}Come here, baby girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.52,1:57:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他非常爱你\N{\reng}He loved you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:27.05,1:57:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅 看看这个\N{\reng}Kya. Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:29.00,1:57:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到上面那个了吗? 在那个树枝的弯处?\N{\reng}You see that up there? On the elbow of that branch?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.62,1:57:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们上次看到这些是什么时候?\N{\reng}When's the last time we saw one of those?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.90,1:57:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\reng}I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.55,1:57:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这本书非常棒 这个人一直都在谈...\N{\reng}This book's pretty good. This guy's still talking about...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.55,1:58:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我希望在我离去的时候\N{\reng\i1}I hope when it is time for me to leave,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.70,1:58:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我会静静的轻松离去 不留一丝声响\N{\reng\i1}I will go quick and easy, without making too much noise.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:25.65,1:58:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈\N{\reng}Ma!
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.37,1:58:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈\N{\reng}Ma.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:33.48,1:58:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈\N{\reng}Ma.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:36.27,1:58:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅?\N{\reng}Kya?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:38.02,1:58:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,凯雅\N{\reng}Kya!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:12.25,1:59:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs17\4c&H000000&\4a&H2E&\pos(192,276)\c&HF6F6F6&\1a&H22&}北卡罗来纳大学保护实验室
Dialogue: 0,1:59:17.07,1:59:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对我来说 能成为...\N{\reng\i1}It has always been enough...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.85,1:59:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}自然循环的一部分已经足够了\N{\reng\i1}to be part of the natural sequence of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:23.86,1:59:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}像潮水般起落\N{\reng\i1}Sure as the tides.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.00,1:59:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}以自然为导向\N{\reng\i1}Nature my guide.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:32.20,1:59:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}沼泽地对死亡了如指掌...\N{\reng\i1}The marsh knows all about death...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:36.97,1:59:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但不一定将其视为悲剧\N{\reng\i1}and doesn't necessarily define it as tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.87,1:59:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当然更不是罪\N{\reng\i1}Certainly not a sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:44.05,1:59:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它懂得每个生物都在为生存做它必须做的事\N{\reng\i1}It understands that every creature does what it must to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:50.80,1:59:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有时 为了猎物的生存 ...\N{\reng\i1}And that sometimes, for prey to live...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:55.10,1:59:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}它的捕食者必须死亡\N{\reng\i1}its predator must die.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:25.02,2:00:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我现在是沼泽\N{\reng\i1}I am the marsh now.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.55,2:00:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我是白鹭的羽毛\N{\reng\i1}I am the feather of an egret.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:31.43,2:00:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我是每一个被冲到岸边的贝壳\N{\reng\i1}I am every shell washed upon the shore.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:37.73,2:00:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我是一只萤火虫\N{\reng\i1}I am a firefly.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:40.15,2:00:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你会看到数以百计的人在沼泽深处向你招手\N{\reng\i1}You'll see hundreds beckoning far into the dark reaches of the marsh.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:44.73,2:00:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那就是你永远能找到我的地方\N{\reng\i1}And that's where you will always find me.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:48.05,2:00:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在最深处\N{\reng\i1}Way out yonder.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:50.00,2:00:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}喇蛄吟唱的地方\N{\reng\i1}Where the crawdads sing.


